title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly peanut butter, margarine and sugars; add egg. Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill. Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
With fork dipped in flour flatten in crisscross pattern to 2 inches.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy saucepan.
Stir on moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil over moderate heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm (about an hour).
Add vanilla and beat just until mixture begins to lose gloss and hold shape.
Requires very little beating.
Quickly stir in walnuts and cherries and turn into oiled pan.
Let stand until firm.
Have used both green and red cherries.

title: double delicious bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° glass).
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Pour milk over crumbs.
Top with both kinds of chips.
Press firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and cut.

title: nuts 'n' bolts
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour over meat, 1 can of soup.
Add green beans, drained.
Add salt and pepper.
Place hash browns on top.
Add the remaining can of soup. Top with the cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°; longer if hash browns hadn't been nearly thawed before adding.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as label directs, using the salt label calls for and reducing cooking time by a minute or two, and drain. Place butter and cream in a hot skillet, add the noodles and simmer for 1 minute. Toss gently with a spoon and fork, add parmesan cheese and pepper until blended.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain and rinse macaroni in cool water. In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate until served.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Blend ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve on cream puffs, bread rounds or crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Form into one-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown and sausage is well done.
Serve warm.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and tear lettuce.
Chop green onions.
Place lettuce in bowl and add onions on top.
Sprinkle 3 Tbsp. of sugar on top of salad mixture.
Fry bacon.
Let cool.
Crumble bacon on top of salad mixture.
Drain bacon grease out of frying pan.
Add 2 Tbsp. of bacon grease to every 3 Tbsp. of vinegar.
Heat until very bubbly; then pour over mixture and toss the salad.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: philly cheesecake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sugar, flour, lemon juice and rind, mixing at medium speed or in food processor until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time; keep mixing.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 300°.
Start checking for doneness after 45 minutes.
Cool, garnish with pie filling and serve.

title: tomato relish
directions: Quarter the tomatoes; chop onions and peppers, then mix all with spices, sugar, vinegar, etc.
Cook until thick about 30 minutes or so.
Seal hot in sterilized jars.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares chocolate with 1/4 cup milk in large, microwavable bowl at High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.
Or heat in heavy saucepan over very low heat. Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pour butter into a rectangle baking dish.
In plastic bag, combine remaining ingredients.
Shake a few at a time, placing potatoes in a single layer.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn slices.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Bake 30 minutes more, or until tender.

title: party punch for 20
directions: Pour
strawberry
soda
into ice cube trays and freeze. Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes and cool.
Add fruit juices to sugar mixture and chill.
When ready to serve, place cubes in bowl and add juice and ginger ale.

title: slaw 1
directions: Make a dressing out of sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and salt and pepper.
Stir with a whisk until mixture is smooth, then pour it over the cabbage.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Brown
onions
in
tablespoons butter.
Mix carrots, salt, pepper,
parsley
flakes,
Cheddar cheese and onion with celery soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and add
cups croutons.
Put on top of casserole the last 6 to
8 minutes
of
baking
time (until they are golden brown).

title: daniel's favorite meat loaf
directions: Smash up ground meat in large bowl.
Add ingredients one at a time; mix very well.
Mold into two loaves.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes on a Pam-sprayed cookie sheet or other suitable pan.
Also can drain off juices as it cooks for gravy.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice thin potatoes.

title: hot (hot) crawfish dip
directions: Saute onion and garlic in small amount of butter. Add crawfish, cream cheese and jalapeno. Cover and cook until cheese melts, stirring occasionally. Add mayonnaise, mustard, sugar and wine. Simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
You may add a little crawfish fat, if desired, also more wine.

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Line Pyrex oblong dish with heavy aluminum foil, leaving an overhang on both sides.
Place brisket, fat side up, in pan and sprinkle with liquid smoke and powders.
Fold up foil and crimp to seal.
Marinate overnight, if possible, but not a must!

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Keeps well for 2 weeks.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Melt bouillon cubes in 1 tablespoons water.
Mix all together and chill.

title: yakisoba
directions: Boil noodles as package directs, drain.
Stir-fry cole slaw and noodles until hot.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg and water.
In a deep 3-quart casserole, combine chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice. Shape meat into balls the size of a walnut.
Place in chili sauce. Heat, covered, in microwave oven for 12 minutes.
Skim off any fat, stir.
Heat, covered, in microwave for 8 minutes or until sauce bubbles and meatballs are cooked.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Beat margarine, peanut butter, 1/2 cup granulated and brown sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add and blend into creamed mixture.
Place 1/4 cup granulated sugar in small bowl.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar to coat.
Place balls 2-inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove cookies from oven; quickly top each with a Kiss; press down firmly.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer to racks; let cool completely.
Store airtight. Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Stir baking soda into applesauce.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 2 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: veal scallopine
directions: Heat electric frying pan to 350°.
Add butter, saute garlic and mushrooms lightly.
Remove.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and dry mustard together.
Dip meat into mixture.
Brown veal in hot butter.
Add tomato juice.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes at 225°.
Add sauteed mushrooms to meat.
Cover and simmer at 225° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: bread pretzels
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the 1 cup warm water.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, butter, salt and sugar and beat for 3 minutes.
Add 1 1/4 cups flour.

title: almond cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add almond extract.
Bake in ungreased 9-inch pie plate for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, in hot butter, cook carrots and onions with garlic until carrots are tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Toss to mix well.
Spoon into buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Cover; bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Garnish with parsley.

title: veal hot dish
directions: Brown meat, celery and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and 1 1/2 cups of juice from peas and mushrooms.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and chill 24 hours before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Mix the vinegar, sugar and salad oil together.
Pour
over vegetables.
Stores in refrigerator for days.

title: cheese delights(these are super easy and everyone always raves!)
directions: Make a paste of the cheeses and mayonnaise and spread on each half English muffin.
Cut in quarters and broil until bubbly and light golden brown.
Makes 48.
Freezes very well.
(Freeze before broiling, then put on sheet and broil when needed.)

title: o'henrys
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and mix well.
Press lightly in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread on top.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Work first 6 ingredients together, like pie crust; add eggs and mix well.
Pat dough into bottom of greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, leaving some of the dough for the top.
Put blueberry filling on top of dough in pan.
Work remaining dough in strips and place crisscross over top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring sugar, water and coffee to a bubbling boil. Then allow to cool. Put in a glass container.
Add vodka and vanilla beans. Let stand for 10 days.
(Add 1 1/2 ounces to a glass of milk for a White Russian or to coffee or over ice for a Black Russian.) Straight in a cordial glass is a great after dinner drink.
An 8 to 10 ounce bottle makes a nice exchange gift or hostess gift at holiday time.

title: cheesy cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease round cake pan. Mix dry ingredients in one bowl; others in separate bowl. Pour into flour mix. Stir well. Pour into pan. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Combine butter, salt, vanilla and 1 cup sugar.
Add milk and remaining sugar alternately, then add peanut butter.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla and nuts real good.
Fold in chocolate chips; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In a 2 cup or slightly larger bowl, combine sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Add garlic salt, chives (or onion salt), parsley flakes and Lawry's salt and stir until blended.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator for one to two hours.
Serve with raw vegetables or may be used as chip dip.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground meat, drain. Combine meat, onions, sauces, soups, and chili. Simmer till blended. Layer meat, tortillas, and cheese., ending with cheese in a 12 x 8 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 350° till cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: herb vinegar
directions: In a quart jar mix the sugar, salt, onions, peppers, garlic and fresh dill.
Fill with vinegar and refrigerate for at least 1 week before using.
Keep refrigerated and use as desired.
To replenish, add more sugar, salt and vinegar as vinegar is used.

title: cocoa black bean soup
directions: Rinse and soak beans overnight in 10 cups water with 1 teaspoon salt and green bell pepper.
In a large heavy 6 quart pot, bring beans, soaking water and pepper to a boil.
Simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Remove green pepper pieces and discard.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Dip skinless chicken in butter then crumb mixture.
Place on cookie sheet covered with tin foil & thin covering of cooking oil or oil spray.
Then, pour the excess crumbs and butter over it.
Bake @ 350° for 45- 60 minutes.
Baste frequently.
DO NOT TURN CHICKEN.

title: pea salad
directions: Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over peas.
Mix 1 tablespoon of sugar with mayonnaise.
Mix everything together and chill.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs slightly beaten.
Sift together 3 cups flour, soda and baking powder and add alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla to the milk.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough that you can handle.
Roll and fill.

title: mrs. j. harris' macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package, adding the salt and oil. In a pot melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine on low flame. Stir black pepper, salt, paparika and 2 tablespoons of flour; mix well, then put 2 cups of milk, continuing to stir.
Add the cheese, cut up in small pieces.
Stir until thick; add your bread crumbs.
Pour sauce over macaroni in layers in a casserole dish and put it in the oven for 20 minutes at 400° or until it browns on top.

title: spinach souffle bake
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish or 3-quart
casserole.
In
large
bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into prepared casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm and set.
This makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings!

title: circle-o skillet supper
directions: In a skillet, cook hot dogs and onion in oil until lightly browned. Combine the next seven ingredients. Mix well. Stir into skillet, bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cook and stir for 2 minutes. Add macaroni. Cook on low heat until heated through.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Slice small green tomatoes thin.
Fill unbaked pie crust with tomatoes, flour, sugar, butter, nutmeg and vinegar.
Cover with crust and bake at 450° until crust begins to brown, then set at 350° and bake until tomatoes are tender.

title: marian's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Beat together margarine, yeast mixture, sugar, egg and salt.
Add warm water and beat in flour gradually until dough is stiff.
Turn onto floured board and knead well until elastic and smooth.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Shape into loaves or rolls; place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise until almost double.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes for loaves, 20 minutes for rolls.
Remove from pan and brush with melted butter.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat in oil in large skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn, bouillon and green pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat. Cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter or margarine until soft, but not brown.
Add crumbs and parsley; mix thoroughly.
Add oysters, bay leaf, seasonings and eggs.
Add enough liquid to moisten. Makes stuffing for 10 to 12 pound turkey.

title: aunt teena's pear relish(old family recipe)
directions: Grind pears, onions and peppers; drain.
Cook all ingredients 30 minutes or longer if you want it to be a little thicker.
Seal in jars.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook pepper, onion and butter until soft.
Stir often.
Add flour, mixed with seasonings and stir until well blended.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly; bring to boil and add corn, egg yolk and bread cubes.
Turn into buttered casserole; cover with cracker crumbs and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour or until crumbs are browned.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat juices from cherries and pineapple.
Dissolve jello in hot juices.
Add Coca-Cola.
Let stand until slightly thickened. Add cherries (cut in half), pineapple and nuts.
Grate cream cheese and add to mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 15.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake in 2 round cake pans and set aside to cool.
Make pudding and set in refrigerator to get cold.

title: easy quiche
directions: Mix eggs with half of milk, then add flour gradually.
Once mixture is smooth, add rest of milk, then meat.
Add other vegetables and cheese, except 1/4 cup to garnish top.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes, then add remaining cheese and bake 15 minutes more.
Test center to be sure it is done.

title: dump salad surprise
directions: Mix together well; freeze.
Take out 20 minutes before serving.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Gradually add other ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: chocolate marshmallow rolls
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Beat egg, sugar and vanilla.
Beat into chocolate mixture.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Form rolls in waxed paper.
Roll in coconut.
Freeze, then slice.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper.
Add meat and cook until done. Add 1/2 cup cheese and rest of ingredients. Cook about 7 ounces or more of spaghetti in salt water until tender. Cover the bottom of a large pan with spaghetti.
Spoon the meat mixture over the spaghetti. Sprinkle cheese over top (3/4 cup mushrooms, optional).
Cover pan and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom stuffed lamb chops
directions: *Ask your meat man to leave on the fell, the thin pieces of meat that extend beyond the chop.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Press cookie dough on buttered pizza sheet.
Bake for 18 to 25 minutes.
Spread on cream cheese the cherry pie filling or strawberry glaze.
Then layer fruit in an attractive manner.
Refrigerate.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing until just moistened.
Pour batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, coated with nonstick cooking spray and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding chocolate chips last. Pour into tube pan (greased and floured, or "Pam" spray).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool, then dust with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate mousse(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Scald milk, chocolate and sugar to almost boiling.
Soak gelatin in the cold water and add to hot mixture.
When cold and slightly thickened, flavor with cinnamon and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze.

title: chocolate cake with peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add melted chocolate and milk; stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: In 2-quart batter bowl, place margarine, onion and celery. Microwave at 100% power for 3 to 5 minutes, or until tender. Blend flour into mixture.
Gradually stir in milk; stir well. Microwave at 100% power for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until thickened. Stir well half-way through cooking.
Stir small amount of mixture into egg yolks, then blend into remaining hot mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese; pour into 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at 100% power for 3 to 4 minutes, or until hot.
Top with cheese; cover.
Microwave at 70% power for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with buttermilk.
Blend in coffee and vanilla.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: 3 layer rainbow salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix lime jello, 1 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour in glass dish and let jell.

title: molly's favorite spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach through colander.
Use spinach, uncooked.
Mix all ingredients; chill.
Use as dip for vegetables, crackers or bread.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta, rinse in cold water and drain well.
Add salad dressing to pasta.
Use all of dressing if you like it real moist, but may want to use all but 1/2 cup dressing.
Mix in Salad Supreme.
Mix very well.
Chop the peppers, onions, mushrooms and olives.
Add to pasta; mix well.
Let stand overnight before serving.

title: quick sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meatballs, cranberry sauce and chili sauce in electric frypan or crock-pot until heated thoroughly.

title: frog eye salad
directions: In small saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Set aside and cool. Cook acini de pepe according to package directions.
Combine cooked mixture with acini de pepe.
Cover; place in refrigerator until chilled.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir lightly. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple macaroon
directions: Drop from spoon over apples sprinkled with sugar and cinnamon. Bake for 30 minutes.
Slice 6 apples in baking dish.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash squash and
trim green ends off.
On aluminum foil squares, place 1 squash, chopped onion and pats of oleo.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roll
foil
up around squash and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pan fried meat loaf
directions: Mix all together (exept for tomato paste and water).
Put 1 tablespoon of tomato paste and 1/4 cup water in a frying pan.
Make hamburger patties round and 1/2 inch thick.
Put in pan.
Put remaining tomato paste on top of meat patties.
Fry slow for 3 or 4 minutes.
Turn over; fry 3 or 4 minutes.
Make sure both sides are brown.
Turn heat to simmer for about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 big burgers.

title: spaghetti sauce(canning recipe)
directions: Put oil, onions and garlic in large pot; cook for 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and bring to a boil; simmer for 2 hours, or until thick.
Remove bay leaves.
Pour into jars and seal.
Set aside for seal to complete.
Eat in 2 months.

title: spiced french toast
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Coat nonstick skillet with Pam.
Drip bread in egg mixture and put in skillet. Brown on both sides.
Makes 4 slices.

title: butter finger cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter together. Add cool whip and crushed candy bars. Break cake into pieces and put in pan. Cover with cool whip mixture. Sprinkle some candy on top.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, egg and buttermilk until creamy.
Blend. Pour vegetable oil into pan.
Coat bottom of pan.
Pour remaining oil into mixture and stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple taffy salad
directions: Mix the miniature marshmallows, pineapple, apples, peanuts and Cool Whip.
Let sit in refrigerator for 8 hours.
Cook in a small saucepan the reserved pineapple juice, flour, white vinegar and sugar until thick and bubbly, approximately 5 minutes.
Cool, then toss with the ingredients.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: seafood ala salad
directions: Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Add Ala and cover.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Drain and cool.

title: cool yogurt smoothie
directions: Place yogurt, 1 1/2 cups whipped topping, fruit and ice in blender container; cover.
Blend until smooth.
Top each serving with 1/4 cup remaining whipped topping.
Serve immediately.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: lobster africaine
directions: Parboil lobster for 5 minutes, after thawing, do not overcook. Drain and remove from shell.
Cut into chunks.
Set aside.
Wrap and refrigerate shells.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, cool and pull from bone.
Save broth from chicken.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Cook onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine until transparent.
Mix all ingredients (except cheese) including 1 cup chicken broth together.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheeses on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grated potato pudding(kugelis)
directions: Dice onion.
Saute with 1/2 cup of water until onion is transparent and water has evaporated.
Stir melted butter (or margarine) into this mixture.
Soak 1 slice white bread in the evaporated milk until completely saturated, stirring to bread it up.
Set aside.
Grate potatoes.
(Shredding with food processor works well.)
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased pan and bake 10 minutes in preheated oven at 400°. Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shirley's chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese and spread over crust.
Mix both puddings according to package.
Spread over cream cheese mixture and top with rest of Cool Whip.

title: crunch potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Add single layer of sliced potatoes; turn once in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over the potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour, or until done and tops are crisp.
Serve hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Let margarine and cream cheese stand to room temperature until soft.
Cream together.
Remove seeds from jalapeno and dice. Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake or microwave until creamy.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions on the box.
Add corn, cheese and soup.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 300° until it bubbles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix tuna, onion, half cashews and cream cheese.
Form ball and roll in rest of cashews.

title: vodka slush
directions: Boil water. Dissolve sugar, lemonade and orange juice. Add tea and vodka. Cool, then place in freezer. Stir occasionally every hour. Serve slush in 8-ounce glass. Add 7-Up.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Put pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over top of pie filling mixture.
Pour melted butter or margarine over cake mix. Bake at least 1 hour or until pumpkin is set in 350° oven.
Can be served with Cool Whip.
Enjoy!!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix ground cranberries and sugar.
Let set overnight.
Drain cranberries for an hour and save juice.
Add grapes and nuts. Stir.
Fold everything together.

title: quick pizza crust
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salad oil. Mix in flour.
Let rise 5 minutes in a warm place.
Roll out and place on pizza pan or cookie tray; let rise again.
Add favorite sauce and toppings.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until crust is brown and toppings are bubbly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk. Add sugar, butter and corn. Add chopped onion. Put in enough crackers to take up some of the moisture. Salt and pepper to taste. Balance of crackers go on top of the mixture after it is placed in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Top with pats of butter. Sprinkle on paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (depending on your oven).

title: spicy honey-roasted peanuts
directions: Combine all ingredients except peanuts and mix well.
Add peanuts and stir until well coated.
Spread in a shallow baking pan. Roast 25 minutes at 325°.
Stir once or twice.
Cool.
Makes 3 cups.
Contains 60 calories per tablespoon.

title: irish cocoa
directions: Beat whipping cream, powdered sugar and vanilla in chilled small mixer bowl until stiff.
Refrigerate.
Prepare cocoa as directed; add 2 tablespoons of cream for each cup.
Pour cocoa in mugs.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put in raw crust.
Combine ingredients together.
Cook at 375° until silver knife inserted comes out almost clean.

title: banana cherry nut bread
directions: Cream margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add bananas; beat well.
Dredge raisins and nuts in 1 cup flour.
Add this to oleo mixture, then add raisins, nuts, cherries and other flour mixture.

title: chow-mein beef bake
directions: In a large skillet, combine beef, celery and onion.
Cook until meat is lightly browned; drain off excess fat.
Add tomato, mushrooms, soup, 1/2 cup of water and half the chow mein noodles; stir until blended.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pass soy sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup. Stand in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Pour undiluted soup in top of pan of double boiler. Add chicken mixture. Blend together. Cover, heat and serve piping hot on toast.
Makes 6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook ingredients until soft ball stage.
Pour over popcorn and stir.
Butter hands and form into balls.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 8X12 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 45-60 minutes.

title: curried couscous pilaf
directions: In a covered saucepan on low heat, saute onion and garlic in butter until soft.
Add mushrooms, red bell pepper, peas and green onions and cook until nearly tender.
Add water or broth, salt and curry powder and bring to a boil.
Add couscous; stir.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir well over popped corn.
Put on buttered cookie sheets, thin layered.
Put in 200° oven for 1 hour. Remove from oven and cool.
Store in covered container to keep crisp.
It helps to take popcorn out of oven and turn it and break it up about 5 times during baking, at about 20 minute intervals.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until set.
(Will not get as firm as jello.)

title: family beef stew
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat beef cubes with mixture.
Brown meat thoroughly in hot oil in a large heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Sprinkle remaining seasoned flour over meat.
Stir well.
Add water and cover.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours, until meat is tender.
Add onions, potatoes and carrots; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Add peas and simmer until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, water, syrup, oleo and salt in saucepan.
Cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring until mixture thickens and spins a string when poured from a spoon.
Add vanilla.
Stir just enough to mix.

title: deli rice pudding
directions: Cook milk, rice and sugar in top of covered double boiler for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Beat eggs until light and foamy. Remove top of double boiler from heat.
Slowly add beaten eggs to rice mixture, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and return to heat.
Continue stirring until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes. Pour into a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cinnamon. Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Blend cream cheese and butter together.
Add confectioners sugar and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful on top of raw cake batter until all used up.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is a moist cheesecake-like dessert.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix in heavy 2-quart saucepan, sugar, marshmallows, evaporated milk, butter or margarine and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over top).
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until completely melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 8-inch saucepan.
Cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: eckrich octoberfest casserole
directions: Pare and slice enough potatoes to make 2 cups.
Set aside. Cook onion in 1/4 cup oleo until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is slightly thickened.
Place 1/2 of sausage in bottom of 2-quart ovenproof casserole.
Add half of potatoes, half of peas and half of sauce.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients, ending with sauce.
Combine crumbs and oleo and sprinkle over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or crumbs are lightly browned.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir
sugar, Karo and peanuts altogether in Pyrex bowl. Put in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Remove and stir; then cook 4 more minutes.
Then add oleo and vanilla; cook 1 minute and
45 seconds.
Add 1 teaspoon soda and stir well.
Pour on greased cookie
sheet
and spread thin.
Cool in refrigerator then break into chunks.

title: fresh apple cake (with shortening)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla, salt, milk, flour and apples. Turn into a greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Mix topping and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible chocolate cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend on high for 1 minute.
Pour mixture into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes or until set.
Cool completely before serving.
Serve topped with whipped cream, nuts, cherries or chocolate sprinkles.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lefsa (norwegian)
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking soda.
Mix in lard like pie crust.
Gradually add water to dough.
Roll with a lefsa rolling pin to desired size.
Cook on hot griddle.
Turn and cook the other side.
(Aunt Anna always put a milk and sugar mixture on one side while cooking.)
Cool.
Stack and cover firmly to hold flat shape.
These will keep for a long time in a cool, dry place.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar.
When ready to serve, put 1 dozen ice cubes and sherbet in punch.
Yields 20 servings.

title: stone soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot, except meat and flour.
Cook meat in skillet (season to taste).
Drain.
Add to pot.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup milk.
Add to soup.
Cook until thickened.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces.
Slice tender part of broccoli.
Add mushrooms, chopped and peeled eggs and onion.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Beat sugars and lard.
Add eggs.
Combine spices, soda and salt with flour and raisins.
Add to beaten ingredients.
Make into a roll or bar and refrigerate.
Cut in slices and put on baking sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: grandmother's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
In a large mixing bowl, pour scalded milk over shortening, butter, sugar and salt.
Stir until shortening, butter and sugar are dissolved.
Add beaten eggs and yeast mixture, then stir in flour until dough is easy to work with.
Knead just a couple of times, then put in a large, slightly greased bowl.
Cover with dish towel and put in warm place and let rise until doubled, about 2 hours.
Knead the dough a couple of times and then roll out on floured surface.
Cut out rolls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet and let rise until double. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Mix everything but chicken together.
Marinate chicken in liquid (vinegar and soy sauce) for several hours if desired. Simmer chicken in liquid mixture until tender, adding water to keep liquid at least an inch in the bottom.
Serves 4.

title: brown rice
directions: Debone chicken breasts.
Cut into long strips and pound to tenderize.
Dip into milk and egg mixture.
Roll into Italian bread crumbs and flour.
Fry quickly in 1/4-inch deep olive oil. Serve with melted butter, fresh lemon or lime slices and fresh tomatoes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In large glass baking dish, add in layers the lettuce, green peppers, peas, celery and onion.
Spread layer of mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Garlic salt is optional. Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix all together, spray large 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Spread mixture in dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in pie shell and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: beef in sherry
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a large buttered casserole. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve on noodles or rice.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt and butter. Keep 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix buttermilk, baking soda and egg. Add to other mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Put in jar or glass bowl and cover for at least 2 days.
Serve with crackers.

title: terri's famous pasta salad
directions: Make pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse well in cold water. Mix mayonnaise and Uncle Dan's in large bowl. Add all other ingredients and mix well. This delicious summer salad tastes best when refrigerated overnight. You can add chicken or tuna if you prefer. Extra mayonnaise may be needed.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Then reduce temperature to 350° for 15 minutes more.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling made of pumpkin pie recipe.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: nutter butter frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla with mixer on medium until well blended.
Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand 1/2 hour before serving.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add liquid ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and sugared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy pizza pie
directions: Cook ground meat, onion and spices until meat is done.
Dice up onion in meat.
Spread on can of rolls on bottom of loaf pan. Spread tomato sauce on rolls.
Spread meat mixture over that, then cheese soup or shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top with other can of rolls and bake until brown as you like.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls and brown in skillet.
Drain off liquid, pour barbecue sauce over meatballs and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: peas and bacon
directions: Fry bacon in pressure cooker.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover securely and place regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 2 minutes, then cool pressure cooker at once.
Thicken sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Cook in oven
minutes, covered.
Take off cover and cook 30 minutes	longer.
Take out of oven.
Put 1 can Chinese noodles on top of casserole and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
In 10 x 6-inch baking dish, layer half the broccoli, half soup mixture and half can onions.
Top with remaining broccoli and soup mixture.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 5 minutes.
Rotate dish after 2 1/2 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Microwave uncovered 1 minute.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together
meat, onion, salt, pepper, egg, bread and ketchup.
Make into balls.

title: 5 hour - no peek - beef stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Layer stew meat (bottom), potatoes, carrot, onion (top) in a covered casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar, pepper and tapioca over the top.
Combine mushroom soup and water and pour over entire mixture.

title: feather rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with sugar.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Scald milk, then add remaining ingredients.
Store in tight container in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out like cinnamon rolls.
Spread with butter.
Roll and slice, then put in a muffin tin.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable casserole
directions: Steam broccoli, carrots and zucchini until crisp-tender; drain and set aside.
Mix together mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and pepper. Add broccoli, carrots, zucchini, remaining vegetables, parsley and basil.
Stir gently to mix.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter.
Add crushed saltines; stir until browned. Remove from heat; stir in Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients, except pie crust.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until well done, approximately 50 to 60 minutes.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Mix and cook in a tube pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: al hirt's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop, reserving whole caps. In a large skillet, melt 1/2 cup butter and add chopped mushroom stems; cook until tender.
Remove pan from heat; add onion soup mix, bread crumbs and sherry.
Mix well.
Fill the mushroom caps with the mixture, mounding it high.
Brush 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle the mushroom caps with Parmesan cheese.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and broil for 5 minutes.
Serve on a platter garnished with parsley (optional).

title: hungarian cabbage rolls
directions: Chop onion into small pieces.
Mix together with hamburger, sausage and rice; add some salt.
In a double boiler, wilt the cabbage rolls.
Put a layer of sauerkraut in the pan, about 1-inch thick.
Take one cabbage leaf and cut the spine off so it will roll easier.
Take a small roll of the meat mix (about 1-inch thick, two-inches long) and roll it up in the cabbage leaf.
Poke the ends of the leaf into the meat mixture to secure it.
Make one layer of cabbage rolls.
Continue process until pan is full.
One layer of sauerkraut, one layer of cabbage rolls, etc.
Stop about 2 inches from the top.
Add water until you can see it; add salt if desired.
Cook on medium burner for 4 hours or until rice is done.
(Open one cabbage roll to see if the rice is done.) Cabbage rolls can be frozen in Ziploc bags and steamed in a double boiler when desired.

title: combination fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges.
Add to strawberry pie filling (can use any flavor pie filling) along with instant pudding mix.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated until used.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup margarine.
Mix on low speed until crumbly.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and pat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: green chile
directions: Roast chilis in a shallow pan at approximately 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Peel and chop the chilis.
Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer to desired consistency. I use a combination of green chili and jalapenos for roasting.

title: crock-pot turkey and beans
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Place on high for a while, then turn on low.

title: robin's ritzies
directions: Spread peanut butter between Ritz crackers, making as many peanut butter crackers as you can from the crackers.
Melt the almond bark according to the instructions on the package.
Dip the peanut butter crackers in the almond bark until each peanut butter cracker is covered.
Put on wax paper and put in refrigerator to cool and harden.

title: apple custard pie
directions: In a bowl, combine Flour and Salt; cut in butter until crumbly. Press onto the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange apples over the crust.
Combine Cinnamon and 1/3 c. Sugar; sprinkle over the Apples.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.
For Custard whisk Milk, Egg and 1/2 c. Sugar until smooth.
Remove pie after 20 minutes and pour Custard over Apples.
Bake at 375 degrees 25-30 minutes longer or until a knife inserted towards the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: italian bread sticks
directions: Roll out bread sticks.
Mix pizza seasoning with melted butter. Dip bread sticks in butter mixture and twist.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet, pressing end of bread sticks down to hold twist. Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: glorified chicken
directions: Brown chicken lightly on both sides.
Add soup and water (1 to 2 cans), salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and let simmer until chicken is tender.
Serve on white rice.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: In bowl, stir together oil, lemon juice, garlic and parsley. Add shrimp; mix well.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Lift shrimp from marinade and drain.
Reserve marinade.
Place on lightly greased grill 2 to 4 inches above a bed of hot coals. Cook, basting several times with marinade, turning once, until shrimp are pink.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour. Add milk, salt, beaten egg yolks and vanilla. Cook in a saucepan over medium heat until thick. Pour into baked pie crust.

title: pear preserves cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat well. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; stir well.
Combine 2 1/2 cups flour and spices; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Dredge pecans in remaining 1/2 cup flour; fold pecans and pear preserves into batter.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; gently fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 waxed paper-lined and heavily greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove layers from pans and let cake cool completely.
Spread Heritage Caramel Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cooled cake.
Yield:
one 3-layer cake.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dump in pie filling and smooth.
Next, dump in the undrained pineapple and smooth.
Do not mix.
Dump in the cake mix, then the nuts, again smoothing, not mixing.
Place butter pieces on top; bake for 1 hour, or until golden.

title: mandarin orange jello(dessert or salad)
directions: Mix the boiling water in the Jell-O.
Add the orange juice. Mix all ingredients and store in a Pyrex 13 x 9-inch dish.
Let set in refrigerator to congeal.

title: cola salad
directions: Drain juices from fruits; heat and dissolve jello.
Add cola and let congeal some.
Mix fruits, cheese and nuts and add to gelatin.
Pour into a mold.
Chill.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Beat 1 minute and spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: smoked sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Heat oil in skillet and fry chopped onions.
Add sauerkraut and simmer a few minutes.
Add the water and sausage; cook until done. Add the grated potato, salt and sugar.
Cook 45 minutes longer.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Spread the coconut over the crust, then drizzle the Eagle Brand milk over the coconut. Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes.
Blend over hot water (not boiling) the remaining ingredients.
Spread over the baked mixture and when cooled, cut in squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash the bananas well.
Cream the shortening and sugar until light.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in the mashed bananas.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the liquid mixture, stirring lightly and quickly and mixing only until blended.
Pour into 2 bread loaf pans (9 x 5-inch) and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut hot potatoes in half.
Scoop out potatoes, reserve shells.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Saute onions in bacon fat; drain.
Mash potatoes with butter.
Add sour cream, onions, salt, pepper and bacon; mix well.
If potatoes seem dry, add a little milk.
Stuff in shells.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Then sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cookie cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
Prepare cake mix as usual.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of crushed cookies.
Fold others into batter.
Pour batter into pans. Bake for 30 to 37 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Crush reserved cookies finely.
Mix into frosting.
Frost cake and enjoy.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomatoes relish
directions: Add all ingredients in large boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for several hours.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking or scorching.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Very good served over vegetables.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package, using 1 cup sugar.
Add remaining juices.
Chill overnight before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: dixie hominy
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until onion and pepper are tender.

title: pebble-top oatmeal bread
directions: In a small bowl, combine yeast, warm water and 1 tablespoon of molasses; let stand until bubbly (about 15 minutes).
In a large bowl, combine margarine, remaining molasses, salt, sugar, 2 cups of oats and boiling water; stir until margarine has melted; add cold water and yeast mixture.
Beat in 4 cups of the flour, 1 cup at a time.
Turn dough out onto a floured board and knead until smooth and satiny (10 to 20 minutes) adding flour as needed to prevent sticking.
Place dough in a greased bowl; turn over to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled (about 1 hour).

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Soften margarine and cheese spread.
Beat together.
Add mayonnaise and garlic salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add crabmeat and mix until well distributed.
Split English muffins.
Spread mixture on muffins.
Freeze 15 minutes and then cut into fourths. If not for immediate use, you can keep them in a container until needed.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: In bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on a wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 30 minutes or until firm.
Meanwhile, melt white coating in double boiler or microwave-safe bowl.
Dip balls and place on waxed paper to harden.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla; divide into 6 parts.
Pat into 9-inch cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 450° until lightly brown. Cool.
Stack layers with dried apple filling, leaving top layer plain.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: *Sprinkle dry pudding on salad.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Dredge in flour.
Brown chicken. Dissolve soup mix in warm water. Combine with tomato paste and pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender and sauce is desired thickness, about 30 minutes. Turn often to keep from sticking.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Brown cut up bacon.
Mix all ingredients together.
Brown in oven at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: cajun potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender; drain. Rinse with cold water; cool completely. Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Place in a large bowl. Add onions, parsley and 3 tablespoons vinegar; toss.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into jelly roll pan and bake at 350° - 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mr. hirschi's cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix all ingredients (except nuts). Shape into a ball and chill.
Roll in the cup of nuts.
If possible, make at least a day ahead to allow flavors to blend.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate the cheese.
Melt oleo.
Mix together.
Add flour, pepper and Rice Krispies or pecans.
Roll into small balls. Press out with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Be careful not to overcook.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Cook the tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, chili powder and salt for 5 minutes. Stir half into meat mixture. Pour the rest over the top and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Wash and trim broccoli.
Cut stalks into spears.
Cook broccoli, covered in boiling unsalted water for up to 10 minutes. Drain.
Meanwhile, in a bowl combine eggs, cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Arrange broccoli in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish; spoon cheese mixture atop.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until egg mixture is set.
Serve immediately.

title: crab and shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in bowl.
Add Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Stir until smooth.
Drain liquid from seafood cans into a cup.
Add about 1/2 of the liquid to the cream cheese mixture and stir.
Flake crabmeat and shrimp into cream cheese mixture.
Stir until evenly mixed.
Chill and serve.
Great with Fritos.

title: lavosh appetizers
directions: For filling, mix cream cheese, beef and onions; add milk sparingly until cream cheese mixture is spreadable.
Spread evenly on softened Lavosh crackers (directions for softening crackers on package).

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and wine in casserole.
Add rice and chicken parts. Cover and bake 1 hour or until rice is cooked.
Remove lid and bake a little longer at 350°.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Thaw bread dough for 4 hours (don't thaw overnight, it will rise).
Roll out bread onto floured surface.
Roll into large rectangle.
Spread dough with mustard.
Layer corned beef, sauerkraut and Swiss cheese on top of mustard.
Roll up filled dough into a tube shape.
Fold ends under.
Pinch ends and seam together.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake according to dough directions.
Periodically, brush dough with milk to aid in browning.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice in salted water until tender and fluffy.
While this is cooking, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk, Cheez Whiz and blend well.
Add broccoli.
Cook about 15 minutes or until tender.
Grease casserole dish with butter.
Spread rice over bottom, pour cheese mixture over rice and cover.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° until lightly brown.

title: eclair cake
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Mix together the pudding mix and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour and spread 1/2 pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers and one of pudding, then top with layer of graham crackers.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, 10 to 12 minutes, in a 350° oven. Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: In a saucepan, mix together milk, onions, peppers and soup. Bring to a boil.
In a casserole dish, place a layer of tortillas, overlapping.
Add a layer of soup mix.
Add cheese layer.
Keep layering until all ingredients are used and last layer is cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, apple and sugar and let set overnight. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add Jell-O, nuts and celery to berry mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, combine corn syrup, brown sugar, eggs, butter, salt and vanilla. Mix well. Pour mixture into pie crust; sprinkle with pecans. Set on cookie sheet and bake until center is done (toothpick test), 45 to 50 minutes. If crust gets too brown, cover with foil.

title: chicken salad amandine with frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil the chicken breasts in lightly salted water until meat is tender.
Let chicken cool. Debone and cut into small strips or pieces.
Fold celery, relish and white pepper into mayonnaise. Fold chicken into mayonnaise mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: homemade meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients well. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix well.
Pour batter into deep dish pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes or until custard sets.

title: appetizer roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add more or less of the sour cream to have a good spreading consistency.
Add chopped onions, cucumber and black olives and garlic salt to taste.
Spread on tortillas. Spread to all but one of the edges.
Roll up, starting on the side opposite this edge.
Place rolls in covered container several hours or overnight.
Slice chilled rolls in 1/2 to 1-inch slices. Can use chopped ham or corned beef and leave out cucumbers. Experiment with combinations.

title: kitchen sink salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together thoroughly in processor.
Makes 1 quart.
(This is the Williams family's favorite salad dressing.)

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff and add 1/2 sugar.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon color.
Add remainder of sugar, lemon juice and rind; fold whites into yolk mixture.
Sift flour and salt; fold into egg mixture.
Bake in ungreased pan for 1 hour.
First 15 minutes bake at 300°, gradually increase temperature to 350° for the last 45 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients over low heat for 1 minute.
Add paprika, mustard, chili powder, cumin, catsup and pepper sauce. Mix well.
Add milk, garlic powder, chopped jalapeno and Velveeta cheese, sliced up for easier melting.
Cook over low heat and stir until it begins to thicken.

title: ham dinner
directions: Brown ham over medium heat.
Put potatoes around meat and sprinkle with sugar.
Reduce heat to low and cook for about 1 hour.
Arrange pineapple slices over ham and pour juice over all. Cook 30 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter, yogurt and sugar.
Add egg whites.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk to butter mixture; add lemon juice and beat well.
Stir in lemon rind; pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomatoes florentine
directions: Remove	stems
only
from
tomatoes,
slice in half and scoop out
middle, about 3/4 ways down.
Steam or boil frozen spinach; drain and squeeze remaining liquid out.
Add spinach and sauteed onions; add dash of nutmeg.
Stuff spinach mixture into
tomato shells.
Sprinkle
with
Parmesan cheese on top. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: egg-drop soup
directions: Bring the first three ingredients to a boil.
Stir eggs into the soup.
For large egg drops, stir the egg slowly.
For small egg drops; stir the egg quickly.

title: popcorn(like crackerjacks)
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt, Karo and margarine; bring to a boil.
Put on low and boil 5 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add vanilla and soda.
Mix with popped corn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: aunt betty's hungarian nut horns
directions: Mix like pie dough and roll out thin. Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: green pea salad
directions: Cut desired amount of lettuce in dish.
Lay thin-sliced onion rings on lettuce.
Pour drained peas on top of onions.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add a layer of mayonnaise.
Top with layer of grated Cheddar cheese.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and sugar until dissolved.
Add bananas, Cool Whip and pecans.
Freeze. Cut into squares and serve frozen. Tastes like banana nut ice cream.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Heat milk.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and stir into hot milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add 3 tablespoons peanut butter and blend well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Prepare chocolate cake mix according to package directions. Pour into an 11 x 17-inch pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Combine flour and milk; cook and cool.
Add 1 cup butter or margarine and sugar.
Beat until fluffy, 5 to 8 minutes.
Spread on cooled cake, keeping it about 1/2 inch from edge of pan.
Melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine and chocolate and cool.
Add egg, vanilla, hot water and powdered sugar.
Beat well and spread on top of cake, even with sides of pan.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Make into 30 meatballs.

title: ham 'n cheese quiche
directions: Line unpricked pastry shells with a double thickness of heavy duty foil.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 5 minutes longer.
Divide ham, cheese and onion between the shells. In a bowl, whisk eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour into shells. Cover and freeze for up to 3 months.
Or cover edges with foil and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Yield:
2 quiche.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Blend well.
Bake at 350°.
A very moist cookie.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, drain.
Add Williams taco seasoning, Ott's famous dressing, kidney beans and picante sauce to meat.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer for 15 minutes.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes and black olives.
Crush chips. Add to meat mixture with desired amount of Cheddar cheese.
Ready to serve

title: 24 hour sour cream salad
directions: Mix fruit and marshmallows.
Let stand 1 hour.
Fold in sour cream which has been stirred.
Place in covered bowl or casserole. Let sit in refrigerator 24 hours.
Fruit cocktail may be substituted for grapes and oranges.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells. Freeze.
Yields 2 pies or 12 servings.

title: seafood stew
directions: Cook onion, celery and potatoes in V-8 juice until potatoes are done. Add lemon juice and seasonings. Add shrimp, scallops and fish. Cook 5 minutes. Add okra and crab for 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: old fashion vegetable soup
directions: Cook salt meat and add potatoes.
Add tomatoes; then pepper and corn.
Add okra last and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread evenly on bread.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Uncover and broil until lightly brown.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Cut
dates,
marshmallows,
orange slices and nuts into small pieces.
Roll graham crackers; mix with small cuts, add sugar
and cream to complete mixture and mix well.
Press into pan lined with wax paper.	Keep wrapped for 8 to 10 days.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil peppers until soft.
Fry hamburger in onion and butter.
Boil rice pilaf in water about 16 minutes or until thawed.
Add to hamburger.
Season with salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Stuff peppers; throw bread crumbs over top.
Drip V-8 juice into peppers.
Add sliced cheese over peppers and tuck sides in.
Coat baking dish with V-8.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a dish; top with chopped pecans. Refrigerate.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternating with milk.
Add poppy seed and flavoring.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from bread pan.

title: apricot-lamb kabobs
directions: Blend together oil, lemon juice, honey, curry powder, salt and garlic. (Reserve some marinade for basting.)
Add lamb.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Remove lamb from marinade and discard juices.

title: cream puff and pie
directions: Boil water and butter together (only until butter melts). Remove from heat.
Add flour and mix (will be glue-like).
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Large bubbles will form but will go down.
Cool.
Pour in mixed pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Butter (or use Pam) a long Pyrex dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, eggs and sugar; add pumpkin.
Put in dry ingredients, then chocolate chips, raisins, nuts and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cornmeal cheddar biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients; cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in cheese and milk just until moistened.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: hot dog and hamburger chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion;
drain off grease.
Add mix, catsup and
water.
Bring
to boil and reduce heat to simmer. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Partially melt chocolate.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Place in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Chill.
Cut when firm.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns; mix with the ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Take 1/4 cup melted oleo and pour over 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Mix well.
Spoon over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cut medium cabbage into 1-inch long thin slices.
Place in a large bowl.
Sprinkle salt over cabbage and toss.
Wait for 15 minutes.
This draws out moisture.
Squeeze remaining water out and place on paper towels for about 2 minutes.

title: cheese spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease 2 quart baking dish. Mix ingredients together and place in baking dish.
Bake for about one hour, check at 50 minutes.

title: bruce's favorite clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Stir in clam liquor, the potatoes and water.
Cook, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add clams, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bible cake
directions: Make like any other cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Loaf pans or layer may be used.
To make more spicy, add 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 teaspoon ginger, 1/2 teaspoon cloves and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add the oil, water and eggs one at a time to the first 3 ingredients.
Beat 1 minute.
Add the strawberries.
Mix well. Bake in 2 round 8-inch cake pans at 350° until done.

title: appetizer tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all of the filling ingredients together.
Divide the filling and spread evenly over each tortilla.
Roll up tortillas. Cover tightly with plastic wrap over each tortilla.
Put in fridge to chill a few hours.
Unwrap; cut in 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch thick slices.
Discard ends.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put peanut butter and margarine in a large bowl and put in microwave.
Melt until it's very runny.
May take 3 times at 1 1/2 minutes each.
Then add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Put in buttered 8 x 8-inch dish and chill in fridge.

title: eggplant shrimp casserole
directions: Preboil
eggplant
until
tender;
drain.
Saute onion, eggplant, garlic and shrimp in the corn oil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in 1/2 cup of bread crumbs.
Pour in greased casserole
dish.
Top
with
sliced
tomato, remaining bread crumbs and cheese.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl. Beat butter, sugars and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased
cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand 2 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix crackers and chips together in a garbage bag.
Mix butter flavor oil and Hidden Valley Ranch mix together; pour over crackers and chips.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: oriental stuffed steaks
directions: Cook
rice
according to package directions until done, about 25	minutes;
cool	slightly.
Stir
in
egg and onion. Preheat broiler.
Using
a	sharp knife, cut a pocket in each steak. Stuff
with
rice mixture.	Broil steaks 4-inches form the	heat until
desired
doneness.
(Allow 4 to 6 minutes on each
side for medium-rare.) Brush often with teriyaki sauce. Garnish with mushrooms and watercress, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: six bean casserole
directions: Form the Italian sausage into 1-inch balls.
Brown in skillet; drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except bacon, in a 5-quart casserole or in a smaller roasting pan.
Partially cook bacon in microwave; arrange over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 16 generous servings.
Great for picnic or barbecue.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pecans evenly on bottom of pan, then spread coconut on top of pecans.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and spread cake batter over pecans and coconut.
Mix together the last three items and spoon on top of cake batter.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and pineapple juice.
Add sugar; mix well. Add ginger ale.

title: frozen rocky road squares
directions: Combine flour, oleo and nuts.
Press in bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Mix pudding mix with 1 cup milk; fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Spread over crust.
Freeze.
Serve with more Cool Whip, if desired.

title: cayle's lemon pie
directions: Juice lemons and mix with Eagle Brand milk.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Stir into pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° in a loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: green bean saute
directions: Reconstitute beef broth with 1/2 cup water.
Saute the first 3 ingredients over medium-high heat in a Teflon frypan for a few minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the 1/2 cup of reconstituted low sodium beef broth and let simmer for a minute or so more, then add the green beans, sliced mushrooms and wine.
Cover and let simmer over medium heat for a few minutes.
Remove cover and simmer until the beans reach the desired tenderness.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring to full boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat until thick.

title: homemade hot chocolate
directions: Good for children to make and give as a gift around Christmas. Serve 1/3 cup mixture per cup of hot water.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef in 3 quart saucepan; drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and water, simmer about 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except lasagne, for filling.
Pour about 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer 3 pieces of uncooked lasagne over sauce; cover with about 1 1/2 cups sauce. Spread one-half of cheese filling over sauce.

title: tootsie rolls
directions: Place margarine and chocolate in a glass bowl and microwave for 60 to 80 seconds on High until melted.
Stir in syrup and vanilla.
Microwave 1 minute.
Combine sugar and milk powder in separate bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients.
As candy thickens, turn out onto waxed paper dusted with powdered sugar and knead until candy is thick.
Divide into 4 or 6 parts and roll into pencil strips using the flat of both hands.
Cut into Tootsie Roll sizes and wrap individually in waxed paper.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: bean dip
directions: Melt cheese and butter in beans, stirring frequently.
Add chopped onions and peppers.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve in container that can be kept heated, such as a crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in freezer.
When half frozen, stir real well.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain grease. Add tomato sauce, salsa and taco seasoning mix. Simmer, stirring frequently

for 5 minutes. In a separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs and oregano. Break tortillas into 1/4 pieces and spread half of the broken pieces on the bottom of a 9 x 13 dish sprayed with a non-stick cooking spray. Top with half of the
meat mix, then the cottage cheese mixture Top with remaining tortillas. Sprinkle the shredded mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake in pre-heated 375° oven for 30 minutes. Remove and let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: jello gelatin - i'm not square
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Firmly press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar. Gradually beat in milk.
Fold in whipped topping and spread over crust.
Top with peaches.
Chill.

title: sesame chicken and celery stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Place in small bowl.
Add sherry, soy and ginger.
Stir to coat.
Stir broth into cornstarch; set aside.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine until done.
Rinse and chill.
Chop green pepper, tomato and cucumber into bite-size pieces.
Mix all together linguine and vegetables.
Mix Italian seasoning and Italian dressing and pour on top.
Stir and chill 10 minutes.

title: ribs in crock-pot
directions: Place ribs and all ingredients in crock-pot. Slow cook 7 to 8 hours with lid tilted.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Mix melted butter with peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Add Rice Krispies and form into balls; place on waxed paper.
Chill. Melt in double boiler or microwave the chocolate chips and wax. Coat chilled balls with chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper and chill.

title: spicy rice-n-rabbit
directions: Cut rabbit into 1-inch pieces.
In a large pan of boiling water, add rabbit and cook at a boil for 1 hour.
In a separate pan prepare rice as per directions.
Drain water from rabbit and combine all ingredients.
Bring to a simmer.
Stir regularly to keep rice from sticking.
Simmer for 10 minutes and serve.

title: hash brown skillet breakfast
directions: In 10-inch skillet with a little oil, cook over low heat hash browns
and onion until underside is crisp and lightly browned. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; stir well and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Cover and cook over low heat until eggs are almost set, about 10 minutes.
Add cheese, cover and cook until cheese melts.
Cut into wedges to serve. Yields 6 servings.

title: dilly bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Microwave 3 minutes on High.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Place in sheet cake pan that is slightly greased.

title: papa poli's frosting
directions: Cook milk, flour and salt over medium heat like a pudding. Stir frequently until very stiff.
Let stand to cool.

title: tomato & cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, stir cheese soup until smooth. Gradually blend in tomato soup, milk and water.
Cup up 5-6 hot dogs and add to soup. Heat, stirring often until all is hot and well mixed.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Heat in microwave 1 1/2 - 2 minutes.
Stir.
Heat at 30 second intervals until melted and smooth.
Pour in a greased pan.

title: astronaut fruit punch
directions: Chill juices before using.
Place all juices in a large bowl and add ginger ale.
Add 2 trays of ice cubes, then float orange slices on top.
Serves 40.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix and keep in jar.
Stir every morning and night.
Keep out 5 days.
After 5 days, start keeping starter in refrigerator and start the following feeding process:

Take starter out of refrigerator every 3 days and feed 3/4 cup of sugar, 3 tablespoons instant potato flakes (not powdered kind) and 1 cup warm water. Stir and leave out all day, 8 to 12 hours, until bubbly.
Take out 1 cup of starter to make bread and return remainder to refrigerator until next feeding.
If not making bread that day, give away that cup or throw out, but it must be removed.
You must continue your "feeding process" as long as you desire to keep a starter on hand for future bread making.

title: chocolate chip applesauce cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: beef house rolls
directions: Bring water, sugar, salt and margarine to a boil and cool to lukewarm. Mix yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water until dissolved. Add to first mixture and egg. Add 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add remaining flour, use more if needed to avoid stickiness. Mix well. No kneading necessary.

title: pasta with chicken and squash
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile, heat cream and butter in a large saucepan until butter melts. Add cheese; cook and stir until melted. Rinse and drain pasta; add to cheese mixture. Cover and keep warm. In a skillet over medium heat, saute onion and garlic in 3 tablespoons oil until onion is tender. Add squash; cook until tender.

Add 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper; remove and keep warm. Add remaining oil to skillet; cook chicken with herbs and remaining salt until juices run clear. Place pasta on a serving platter; top with chicken and squash. Yield: 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie shell per package directions for this type of pie. Preheat oven to 425°. Mix the first 6 ingredients. Stir until well blended, then add the next 3 ingredients. Stir until mixture is smooth. Pour pumpkin mixture into the pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for another 35 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from the pie edge comes out clean.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix Jiffy cornbread as to instructions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch greased glass casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot hominy
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter.
Add hominy, tomatoes, sausage and seasoning to taste.
Cook for 20 minutes.
In greased casserole, layer hominy and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: red neck caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients, cover and refrigerate.
Better if made day before.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: spiced roast chicken
directions: Prepare Stuffing:
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, heat olive oil.
Add onion and saute for 2 minutes or until soft. Stir in Garam Marsala and cook 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, parsnips and carrots.
Cook, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts, fresh thyme, bread crumbs, egg and salt and pepper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients at room temperature. Form into a ball and roll in reserved pecans.

title: zucchini cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice zucchini crosswise and boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients.
Layer zucchini in 2-quart buttered casserole alternating with sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: creamy rice pudding
