directions: Combine rice, sugar, salt and milk and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; cover.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour.
Slightly beat eggs; add some of the hot rice mixture to eggs, then stir into rice; add cinnamon and raisins.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: italian zucchini bake
directions: Wash squash; trim ends.
Cut in half lengthwise and parboil for 5 minutes, or until just crisp-tender.
Remove from heat; rinse with cold water.
Drain thoroughly, even squeeze the squash a bit to extract all liquid.
Slice into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop and set pecans aside.
Let cream cheese soften.
Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese mixing until well blended (using your hands).
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill. Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts for covering.

title: microwave potatoes au gratin soup
directions: Combine water and vegetables in 2-quart casserole dish, cover. Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes, until potatoes are tender-crisp.
Stir in broth, cheese, cream and peppercorns. Cover.
Microwave on Medium-High for 5 minutes, until hot.
Remove peppercorns and stir.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken 30 minutes.
Boil broccoli 30 minutes.
Cut chicken into smaller pieces and layer with broccoli in casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayo, milk, curry powder, salt and pepper.

title: crystal's dip
directions: Use 10-inch pizza pan.
Spread cream cheese over the bottom of pan.
Add, in the order given, all remaining ingredients.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn-rice bake
directions: Prepare rice with 1 cup water (no salt) as directed on package label.
Add cream-style corn, eggs, pimentos, onion, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons melted butter or margarine.
Put 1/2 of mixture in 9-inch pie pan (or bake dish).
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Add remaining mixture and top with 1/2 cup more cheese. Dot with 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Enjoy.
(Ken Muhlenbruck.)

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken in pan and add water to cover.
Bring to boil and then reduce heat.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from pan.
Remove chicken from bones and set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together, top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Steam zucchini.
Plunge into cold water; dice when cool. Combine with oil, vinegar, chopped onion, chopped pimento, crushed garlic, salt, pepper, diced pepper and chopped olives.
Let marinate.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and 1 cup sugar well.
Beat in vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda, powder and salt.
Beat dry ingredients into sugar mixture alternately with sour cream. Beat well.
Grease and flour a 9-inch tube pan.
Combine brown sugar with remaining granulated sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle a little of this in the bottom of pan.
Make 3 layers each of batter and nut mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Remove from oven.
Let set 5 minutes, then turn out on cake rack.
Cool.

title: hot wassail
directions: Put the liquid in bottom of a 30-cup percolator.
Put the spices and sugar in the top.
Let perk.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, onion and tomatoes in a salad bowl.
Bring to a boil sugar, salt, dry mustard, lemon juice and ketchup.
Pour hot over salad; crumble bacon and toss.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until brown. Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in greased 10-inch quiche pan or pie plate.
Sprinkle with chilies.
Combine milk, egg and Bisquick.
Pour over all.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and top with sliced tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Best if 2 small loaves instead of 1 large.

title: easy bake pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef until done.
Drain. Place biscuits on cookie sheet and press out flat.
Put catsup on each biscuit.
Next, put cooked ground beef on catsup and top with grated cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese melts and edges of biscuits turn brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Cover bread with milk for five minutes. Add sugar, eggs, butter, salt and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Mix well and pour into buttered dish.
Set dish in pan of warm water and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar before baking.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped walnuts and chill.
Recipe can be cut in half for a smaller cheese ball.

title: texas straw hats
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion, celery and green pepper in hot butter until tender, not brown.
Add beef; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients except chips and cheese.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over corn chips.
Top generously with cheese.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter for 6 minutes.
Pour over 1 large jar of Marshmallow Creme and chocolate.
Add vanilla.
Stir until stiff.
Pour into a large sheet cake pan, which has been buttered. Chill before serving.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Mix in very large bowl; chill until serving time.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Split chicken breasts.
Roll up 1 thin slice of beef and insert.
Wrap slice of bacon around breast.
Secure with toothpick. Mix sour cream, soup, salt and pepper; pour over breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and almond extracts.
In small bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in sour cream and peaches.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Add all ingredients in large bowl. Gradually add milk until you form a doughy substance. Knead for 5 minutes. Let stand for 30 minutes.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut top off of potato instead of cutting in half.
Mix potato, chives, sour cream, grated cheese, salt, pepper, onion and enough milk to have desired consistency.
Put back in oven.
Sprinkle some grated cheese on top and bake to reheat.

title: mustard dressing
directions: Heat 1 cup water and 1 cup vinegar.
Mix egg, sugar, mustard, turmeric, salt and flour.
Stir into water and vinegar.
Watch it. Don't burn on the bottom of pan; double boiler works good.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix all ingredients together.
Blend well.
Pack in graham cracker box lined with wax paper or in Tupperware ice cream container lined with aluminum foil.
Set in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days before serving.

title: drumstick delight
directions: Wash chicken legs in cold water.
Debone legs, leaving 1/2-inch at stick end.
Combine all ingredients (except chicken legs)
in bowl and mix by hand until well mixed.
Stuff chicken legs with mixture until plump.
Place in a baking pan and brush with your favorite barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda, salt and cocoa. Mix well.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water and add boiling water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool and add mayo, lemon juice, onion, hot pepper sauce, paprika and salt.	Mix well.
Add seafood and capers.
Beat well.
Fold cream into mixture and turn into 2 quart fish mold or bowl.
A layer of seasoned cottage cheese may be added to fill out the mold.
Chill 4-6 hours and unmold. Garnish with sliced cucumbers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: potato roquefort soup
directions: Clean leeks well.
Cut green onions into 2-inch julienne strips.
Heat butter in large pan.
Cook leeks 4 to 5 minutes. Add garlic and potatoes.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken stock and salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Puree in a food processor.
Replace in cooking pot and heat on medium heat.
Whisk all but 1/4 cup of cheese and Prosciutto ham into soup.
When cheese is melted, add milk.
Saute Prosciutto ham and green onions and serve as garnish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of hot soup.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
(Be sure to stir milk until smooth to spread evenly.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Freeze well.

title: chinese barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Combine ingredients; cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Brush onto ribs and barbecue.

title: john's dip
directions: Put in crock-pot until cheese has melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Melt some butter and spread in baking pan.
Mix all ingredients, except noodles, in large bowl.
Boil noodles as directed on package.
Add to mixture.

title: drunken dogs
directions: Cut up hot dogs into bite-size pieces.
Put in pan with wine, sugar and ketchup.
Cook over low heat until hot dogs are coated thoroughly.
(No liquid left.)

title: pistachio salad
directions: Do not drain the pineapple.
Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lolly's beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Put in crock-pot and cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Fry ground beef and onion until browned.
Add sprinkling of garlic powder, cumin and small amount of ginger.
Stir in chili mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: goggin's noodles
directions: Crack egg into large mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 egg shell full of water and salt.
Mix slightly.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Mix well.
Knead on floured board 3 to 5 minutes.
Roll out small amounts into thin sheets and set aside to dry.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add all ingredients except pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Add your pecans but do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then turn down to 275° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream or topping.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mix into a 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 of wafers and 1/3 bananas. Add another layer of pudding.
Repeat layers with wafers and bananas and pudding, making last layer pudding.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Beat egg whites until frothing or stiff.
Dip whole walnuts in egg whites, then into mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on cookie sheet at 300°.

title: spicy vegetable pasta
directions: Break linguini into thirds and cook according to package directions.
Combine linguini, vegetables and salad dressing; sprinkle with salad seasoning and cheese.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: jumbo chipits oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, brown sugar, granulated sugar, egg and vanilla in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine, in separate bowl, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips (jumbo).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Garnish with coconut, if desired.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift flour and salt in bowl; cut in shortening until mixed. Combine egg and water.
Add flour; mix well.
Roll out half of dough to fit bottom and sides of pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Fill with apples.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in saucepan.
Blend in water; cook until thick.
Pour over apples.
Roll out other half of dough; put over top and cut slits.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost with thin icing when nearly cool.

title: cheesy cabbage casserole
directions: Break leaves from cabbage head and place in cold water to cover for 5 to 10 minutes. Drain well. Cut into 1/2-inch strips, removing ribs.
Place in boiling salted water to cover. Cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes and drain well.
Place half the cabbage in a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole. Spread half the soup and half the cheese.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper.
Repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with milk.
Add butter, sugar and eggs.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add the vanilla.
Bake in layers at 365° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes four layers.

title: buenelos
directions: Mix and reserve first 4 ingredients.
Beat egg into 1/4 cup milk until blended.
Add dry ingredients.
Warm 2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup milk.
Add to mixture; roll out to about 6-inch diameter.
Cook in pan with hot oil.
Turn over when it becomes crisp.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: wassail
directions: Squeeze and save juice of oranges and lemons.
Combine orange and lemon peel, water, cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Simmer 1 hour and strain.
Add cider, orange and lemon juice.
Reheat but do not boil.
Makes 24 cups.

title: green bean stir fry
directions: Heat olive oil in nonstick pan.
Season meat with garlic and pepper.
Brown meat in pan, 3 minutes each side.
Add onions and green beans and margarine.
Stir until onions are soft.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Wash all vegetables; cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Slice radishes and green onions.
Toss together lightly.
Cover with just enough Hidden Valley Ranch Style dressing to coat vegetables lightly.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture and beat smooth.
If too thick, add milk; if too thin, add flour.

title: kielbasa and cabbage with boiled potatoes(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Make on top of stove in large Dutch oven pot or bake in 300° to 350° oven in large roasting pan.
Do not let liquids dry up; add water or beer as needed.
Chop cabbage into quarters and separate layers apart into pot.
Slice onion and separate rings into pot on top of cabbage.
Scrub carrots and slice into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Leave skin on apples; wash and slice into wedges or chunks.
Add liquids, sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cover and cook in oven 1 1/2 hours or longer; stove top also 1 1/2 hours or longer.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add baking powder and beat until stiff, adding sugar slowly.
Cover pie with meringue and brown in hot oven.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind all vegetables with coarse grinder or chop fine.
In a large kettle or canner, combine all ingredients.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes, stirring.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Approximate yield is 5 pints.

title: marie's meat casserole
directions: In greased baking dish, put a layer of onions.
Add layer of carrots and a layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to cover potatoes.
Add meat patties last.
Bake at 325° until carrots are tender, approximately 1 hour.

title: rice cooker cabbage casserole
directions: Measure rice and water in rice cooker measuring cup. Mix all ingredients in large pan or bowl; pour in 8 to 10-cup cooker and start machine. After bell rings, let stand 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Mix both sugars, margarine and egg in a large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt (dough will be stiff); stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cookies cool slightly then remove from cookie sheet with a spatula.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, all but croutons, in a large casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 15 minutes, after putting croutons on top.
Serve warm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown
the
ground
beef; drain, season with soy sauce. Add drained green beans;
pour mushroom soup over beans.
Top with onion
rings.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.
Lower oven rack will prevent burning of onion rings.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, jelly and eggs.
Dissolve soda in milk and add to creamed mixture.
Gradually add half the flour, sifted with spices.
Dredge nuts and fruits with remaining flour and stir into batter.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon onto buttered and floured cookie sheet.
Decorate tops with sliced candied cherries, if desired.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
These cookies ripen just as fruitcake does.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: dirt salad(really a dessert)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cookies.
Blend well.
Place in a clean plastic "Flower Pot" six inches across the top.
Use a white one for contrast with the cookies.
Place crushed cookies over pudding mixture so it looks like dirt.
Use a plastic or silk flower to garnish.
Chill and serve.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat sugar, butter and flour well.
Add eggs and mix well. Add pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour.

title: hamburger patties with gravy
directions: Make ground beef into patties.
Roll in flour.
Brown in fat on both sides.
Make sure patties are well browned.
Mix other ingredients in a cup.
Pour over meat patties; add water.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: quick pepper steak
directions: Cut steak, green peppers and onion into 1/2-inch strips. Brown in 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet, stirring frequently. Stir in 1 cup water, brown gravy mix and soy sauce.
Cover; simmer 10 to 15 minutes until tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix in glass bowl and microwave 9 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Boil jars and lids before packing.
Best if chilled in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
In saucepan, put the margarine, sugar, beaten egg and Carnation milk. Bring to good boil, stirring constantly.
When it begins to thicken, remove from heat.
Add the graham cracker crumbs, chopped pecans and coconut; mix well.
Spread on graham crackers.
Put another layer of whole graham crackers on top.
Cool, then top with frosting.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Follow directions on box of stuffing; instead of water, add broth.
Mix broth, salt, pepper, soup and milk together in baking dish.
Put enough chicken in as you desire, then add stuffing on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, that is 1/2 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: millionaire pie
directions: *Baked crusts can be used.

title: oven-baked potato strips
directions: Scrub potato.
Cut lengthwise into strips, about 1/2-inch thick.
Pat strips dry with paper towel.
Toss strips with oil in bowl.
Spread strips in a single layer on a cookie sheet.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 450°.
Turn strips every 5 to 6 minutes during cooking process to allow for even browning.
Toss with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 1 serving.
Serving size is 1 (3 ounce) potato.

title: spanish delight
directions: Brown meat in small amount of cooking oil in frying pan. Drain excess grease.
Add chopped onion when meat is partially browned.
To this mixture, add tomato paste, corn, salt and pepper to taste and a dash of sugar.
Allow this mixture to simmer a few minutes, then add the cooked noodles or macaroni.
Place in large casserole dish (13 x 9-inch) and cover with grated cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°), uncovered, long enough to melt cheese.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Over medium-high heat in a medium sized frying pan, melt the margarine.
Add the parsley and onion and saute until the onion is tender.
Add the lemon juice and garlic; stir and continue to saute, about another 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp and salt.
Stir to mix well.
Saute until the shrimp are opaque and turn pinkish, about 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni and layer in baking dish with 1/2 of macaroni, 1/2 of sausage (drained) and 1/4 package of pepperoni, 1/2 jar of spaghetti sauce and a layer of Mozzarella cheese (1/2 package).
Repeat the layers.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until cheese is melted.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cover and cook onions in margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and add shrimp.
Pour shrimp sauce over.

title: grandmom's orange bread
directions: Pour juice of orange into 8 ounce measuring cup; add boiling water to fill cup.
Grate orange and add to juice and water.
Pour into bowl.
Stir in shortening and vanilla.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients and stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients. Beat well.
Add nuts.
Grease bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. When done, turn onto rack and cool.

title: cinnamon yeast rolls
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs and set aside.
Place yeast and water in small bowl and sprinkle with a little sugar and allow yeast to activate.
Mix eggs and yeast mixture together.
Add flour to egg mixture in large bowl.
Mix until slightly sticky and then knead by hand on floured surface until smooth.
Place in a large covered bowl overnight or let rise in warm location for about 2 hours.

title: citrus grape drink
directions: In a saucepan, heat water and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Pour into a large pitcher or punch bowl.
Stir in the juices.
Serve over ice. Yield: about 2 quarts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and drop dough on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and meal.
Add eggs, butter, buttermilk and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Soften oleo.
Mix all ingredients.
Make in small balls. Flatten.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
May top with bacon.

title: pail pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.
Let set for 10 days.
Keep refrigerated.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill.
Serve with vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: red christmas punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add juices.
Chill until serving time.
Put ice cubes and punch mixture in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: dump it in cobbler
directions: Melt
the
margarine.
Pour it into a baking dish.
Mix the sugar,
flour
and	milk.
Put the mixture in baking dish. Pour it over
the	margarine.
Don't mix.	Dump the fruit in. Don't mix. Bake
at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm, topped with ice cream.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot fat.
Cook until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: spinach pudding
directions: Make an "X" cut in each package of spinach.
Place both packages on a plate and microwave on 100% power for 8 to 9 minutes, until thawed.
(Times may vary, depending on microwave oven size and power.)
Drain well.
Mix together spinach, cottage cheese, salt, Parmesan cheese and eggs until well blended.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on 100% power for approximately 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with a little additional Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Drain the beans; put them in a 6-quart heavy pot with ham bone.
Add 3 quarts fresh water.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour.
The beans must be covered with water at all times.
Add water if needed.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Add more water, to cover, if needed.
Simmer, partially covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until liquid has thickened.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar and oil. Sift into it the flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Blend in the pumpkin. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy party punch
directions: Combine ingredients in order given and serve on ice.
Serves 50.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: *Sulfate-phosphate (double-action) type.
Use 4 teaspoons tartrate or phosphate type.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with Pam cooking spray; line with chips.
Top with cooked, chopped chicken.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Lay pieces of chicken on washed rice in a Pyrex dish.
Mix onion soup, water and celery soup; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: steak in foil
directions: Line pan with foil.
Put 1/2 of onion soup mix in bottom of pan.
Place meat on top of mix.
Put remaining soup mix on top of the meat.
Cut carrots in thin circles and place on top of soup mix.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Put foil over pan and seal.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pork pie
directions: Cook together.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream and set aside.
Brown hamburger.
Add onion, seasonings and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer on low heat 20 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer half the noodles.
Spread half the cream cheese mixture over noodles.
Place half the meat over cream cheese.
Repeat.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly.
May be made the night before and placed in refrigerator.

title: lemon bars
directions: Ronald Regan enjoyed light desserts, often flavored with lemon, during his two terms in the oval office.
Lemon squares were served at the Arkansas Governor's mansion during the Clinton years.
Try this recipe for lemon bars made with Minute Maid lemon juice.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, water, 5 1/2 tablespoons butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil; set aside.
Separate dinner rolls and roll thin.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of pie filling into middle of each piece of dough. Fold over and seal edges.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg.
Dot with remaining butter.
Pour sugar mixture over dumplings.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until brown, basting often.
Yields 8 dumplings.

title: very moist coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together condensed milk and cream of coconut.
Punch holes in sheet cake and spoon coconut mixture over cake while hot.
When cake is cool, spread whipped topping on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Set aside.
Remove core from cabbage.
Place in a large pot (with lid) of water and steam until leaves remove easily.
Roll ground meat mixture in cabbage leaves.
Take frying pan, add butter and flour.
Brown flour in butter.
Add red pepper.
Mix well.
Add this to pot with rolled cabbage.
Let simmer for about 2 hours or until done.

title: unusual fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add sour milk.
Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.

title: candied pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water in a large bowl until frothy. Add pecans and mix well. Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon. Add to nut mixture.
Place on buttered cookie sheet. Bake at 225° for 1 hour. Turn every 15 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: In bowl, mix meat with 1/2 can tomato sauce and remaining ingredients; set remaining tomato sauce aside.
Shape meat mixture into a loaf and place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour; drain.
Pour reserved tomato sauce over meat loaf and bake 5 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked cheese grits(makes 18 to 24 servings)
directions: Combine water and salt; bring to a boil.
Stir in grits; cook until done, following package directions.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and 11 1/4 cups cheese; stir until completely melted.
Add a small amount of hot grits to eggs, stirring well.
Stir egg mixture into remaining grits.
Pour grits into a lightly greased steam table pan; sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick tomato rice for kids
directions: Prepare rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add spices, salt and pepper. Add frozen broccoli; stir until thawed and well mixed.
Add soup and mix well; add cheese and stir until melted.
Add cooked rice and mix.
Cook in buttered casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli rice bake
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain; add to sauteed mixture.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz; bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes with cover.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onion, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush cornflakes and stir in remaining margarine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with lemon twist or parsley.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: classic potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water in large saucepan for 8 to 10 minutes or until fork-tender; drain.
Toss potatoes with remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole; cover.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender and Velveeta is melted. Stir gently before serving.
Makes 7 servings.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Place in large mixing bowl.
Mix well and let stand 20 minutes, stirring often.
Take one box fruit pectin, mix 1/2 cup water and mix well in a small saucepan.
Place over low heat and stir until it comes to a boil.
Let boil 1 minute.
Pour immediately over the berries and stir an additional 2 minutes. Pour into containers and let stand overnight.
Berries may then be placed in freezer.
Very good over everything!

title: corn dogs
directions: Make batter.
Dip hot dog in deep hot oil.
I make a ketchup, mustard and salad dressing dip.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine moist ingredients, blending well. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 3 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Cream well.
Mix in all dry ingredients.
Mix well and drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix all together, except Ritz crackers and melted margarine. Top with the crushed crackers and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mock lasagne
directions: In skillet, brown meat and drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, water, garlic salt, pepper and basil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix rice, ground beef, onion, salt and pepper together.
Form round balls.
Put in baking kettle.
Mix tomato soup with 1 1/2 cans water and pour over meatballs.
Cook in oven, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate; take off heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Heat oven to 350°; bake for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hungarian chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve powder and soda in the one cup of hot coffee; mix well.
Add to the cake batter and blend.
Batter will be runny! Pour into 9 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue spareribs sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes or until slightly thickened. Spread on ribs and broil or cook on outdoor grill, basting often.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except sugar.
Boil 15 minutes.
Strain through a cloth.
Add 3 cups sugar or 2 cups if cranberry sauce is used.
Serve hot.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix and cook.
Add to prebaked pie shell.

title: cheddar taters
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. Gently stir in the Tater
Tots. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer the bottom of pan with refried beans.
In mixer, beat cream cheese, sour cream, chilies, taco seasoning and salsa. Place this layer over beans. Arrange a layer of cheese and lettuce.
On top
of lettuce, place olives, green onion and cherry tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine with Hellmann's mayonnaise, enough to moisten salad. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: icebox butterhorn rolls
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Add milk, sugar, egg, salt and 3 cups of the flour. Beat until smooth; beat in butter and remaining flour. Dough will be sticky. Do not knead. Place in greased bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight or all day. Punch down and divide on a floured surface. Roll each half into a 12-inch circle. Cut each circle into 12 pie shaped wedges. Roll each wedge, beginning at the wide end. Place rolls point side down 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Brush tops with melted butter. (Yields 2 dozen.)

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop or tear lettuce; dice tomatoes and cut purple onion up fine.
Toss these 3 ingredients together.
Cook ground beef; drain any grease.
Drain the can of red beans.
Add to the lettuce mixture and toss all together again.
Add Doritos corn chips, broken up slightly.
Add dressing.
Serve with French bread, spread with margarine and Parmesan cheese and heated.

title: cheeseburger mac
directions: Brown meat in large skillet. Drain. Stir in water, catsup and onion powder. Bring to a boil. Stir in macaroni. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover. Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Add Velveeta. Stir until melted.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, sugar and soda; set aside.
In skillet, boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Mix flour mixture into chocolate mixture and add the beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; stir well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: delores' dill potatoes
directions: Melt margarine.
Add dill weed, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Layer potatoes and onions in microwavable casserole, pouring margarine mixture after each layer.
Microwave on High until tender.
Cover with wrap to prevent drying out.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery, 1 teaspoon salt and boiling water in deep pot or kettle.
Cover.
Simmer until tender, about 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine
first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Spread half of mix
in
8	x
x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Cover with chilies and cheese slices.	Pour other half of corn mixture on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; if you plan to bake immediately, water should be lukewarm. If you plan to store dough in refrigerator for

later use, dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and cold water for the other 1 1/4 cups. Sift flour and sugar together. Cut in solid shortening or oil. Add yeast water. Since this recipe gives you a rather sticky dough, mix using a sturdy spoon (wooden is fine) until well blended. Keep stirring until dough forms elastic-like strands when you pull spoon out. Place dough in well-greased bowl; cover. If you want hot rolls tonight, let rise 30 minutes. If you want to bake later, cover bowl well and put into refrigerator.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in hot water until soft.
Add sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and beaten egg yolks.
Add vanilla.
Pour in baking dish and cook for about 40 minutes at 350°.
Beat egg whites and use for meringue, adding 6 tablespoons of sugar in egg whites while beating.
Brown in oven.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with cake mix (dry), nuts and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix quickly.
Add nuts and coconut if adding. Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper; let stand 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: sugar free banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas in large, flat bowl.
Beat milk into pudding until thickened.
Pour over bananas and spread to cover.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Chill before serving.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Saute garlic in butter and remove from heat.
Add chicken and let set for 3 minutes in hot butter, turning to coat each piece.
Dip in bread crumb mixture.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with foil and chill.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Add sugar to creamed oleo; cream.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion, sugar, salt, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce in bowl; pour mixture in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole ending with toast cubes.
Pour butter over toast. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix well first six ingredients.
Add grated squash.
Mix well. Bake at 350° to 375° until golden brown or until pie is firm, approximately 45 minutes.
Tastes like coconut pie.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Mix
powdered
sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese until smooth.
Spread
over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: my oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to margarine mixture, mixing well. Stir in oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes. (If you want a crisp cookie, 10 to 11 minutes.)
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to cooling rack.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup hot water.

title: carrot salad(another great "make ahead" dish)
directions: Chop carrots into bite size pieces and boil to crispy-tender. Mix Italian dressing to package directions.
Drain cooked carrots and while they're hot, pour dressing over them.
Let them marinate, the longer the better they are (up to 1 week).
Stir occasionally.
Serve at room temperature.

title: apple meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Form into loaf and place in 10 x 14-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let sit for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: In small bowl melt butter and cheese together.
Add crabmeat and stir until blended.
Spread on Ritz crackers on cookie sheet. Broil until very lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg and peanut butter.
Mix salt and soda into flour.
Add flour, oats and vanilla to first mixture. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Dampen hands and press mixture so it covers the bottom of the pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
(Do not overcook.)
After removing from oven, sprinkle the chocolate chips over top.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread.
Over this, drizzle a mixture (mix well) of the peanut butter, powdered sugar and milk.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: In bowl, blend soups, butter and rice.
Place in greased oblong casserole.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Brush top with extra melted butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: yogurt-sesame chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl; set aside. Combine yogurt and honey.
Dip each piece of chicken in yogurt mixture.
Dredge in cornflakes mixture.
Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: With electric mixer, beat cream cheese well.
Microwave marshmallow cream for 30 seconds.
Add to cream cheese.
Blend in sugar and food coloring.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven. After 20 minutes, remove from oven and mix well.
Return to oven and finish baking.

title: danish sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light.
Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; blend well.
Make little balls.
Press flat with a glass onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes light, sweet crispy sugar cookies.

title: bean sprout salad
directions: Rinse bean sprouts, removing any green shells that may be left.
Place in large colander and pour boiling water over sprouts to blanch.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with sprouts. Serve warm or cold.

title: smoked sausage and sauerkraut casserole
directions: Place sausage in large skillet with 1/3 c. water. Cover; bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat to low; simmer covered, 10 minutes. Uncover and simmer until water evaporates and sausages brown lightly. While sausage is cooking, combine sugar, mustard, caraway seeds and dill in medium saucepan; stir until blended. Add sauerkraut and bell pepper; stir until well mixed. Cook, covered, over medium heat 10 minutes or until very hot. Spoon sauerkraut mixture into microwavable 2 to 3 qt. casserole; sprinkle with cheese. Stir sausage into sauerkraut; cover. Microwave on HIGH 30 seconds or until cheese melts. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken san francisco
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Brown in butter until golden.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Add wine. Simmer 10 minutes or until onions are soft.
Stir in sour cream and spices.
Simmer 5 minutes longer, tossing gently several times.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tortilla bites
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on flour tortillas. Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into bite size pieces and serve with picante sauce.

title: cheddar batter bread
directions: Grease an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of cornmeal; set aside.
In a large bowl, stir together 1 1/2 cups of flour, yeast, onion powder and pepper; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine milk, sugar, margarine and salt.
Heat and stir just until mixture is warm and margarine is almost melted.
Add warm mixture to flour mixture.
Add eggs; beat with mixer on low-medium speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl.
Beat on high 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese and the 1/2 cup cornmeal.
Stir in remaining flour; batter will be soft and sticky. Turn into prepared pan.
Cover and rise in warm place until nearly doubled (20 minutes).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
If necessary, cover with foil last 15 minutes to prevent overbrowning.
Remove bread from pan; cool.

title: broccoli and noodles supreme
directions: Cut chicken breasts in bite size pieces.
Saute until done. Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: tasty cheese puffs
directions: Soften cheese; crumble sausage, cheese and salt into Bisquick. Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Freezes well.
Yields 90 balls.

title: carob tofu cream pie
directions: Melt carob chips and honey in saucepan over boiling water. Blend in blender with tofu.
May need to add a little hot water to thin mixture slightly.

title: cranberry and chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle soup over it.
Spoon cranberry sauce over soup.
Pour French dressing over all of it and bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 1 hour.

title: double chocolate sugar cookies
directions: Melt 1 c. chips in microwave, reserve remaining chips.
Set both aside.
Beat butter at medium speed until fluffy.
Gradually add 1 c. sugar, beating well.
Add egg, milk, and vanilla, mixing well.
Add melted morsels, mixing until blended.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; gradually add to butter mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in remaining chips.
Roll dough into balls, then roll in 1/2 c. sugar.
Place on cookie sheets and bake at 400° for 8-10 minutes.
Let sit 1-2 minutes after removing from oven, then transfer to cooling racks. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: mansion tortilla soup
directions: Cook chicken breasts until well done.
Chop and reserve meat and stock.
In 1 tablespoon corn oil, saute garlic, onions and tomatoes for 5 minutes (do this in a large heavy pan).
Add beans and corn.
Simmer until heated through, then add chicken broth, pepper and cumin.
When this has heated through, add the chopped chicken.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together using half of cheese. Spread about 1/2 cup on each tortilla and roll up, placing seam side down in pan.
Pour remaining mixture on top of tortillas and top with remaining cheese and olives.
Microwave on high 10-12 min.
or bake at 350° 15-20 min.

title: hot rolls(yields 50)
directions: Add yeast and sugar together, then add to very warm (not hot) water. Let yeast rise. In another bowl, add dry milk, salt and flour together. Add oil to yeast, then add flour mixture. Beat until mixture pulls away from bowl; cover and let rise, then knock down and let rise again. Make out into loaf or rolls. Let rise again and bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except small Cool Whip.
Beat on medium for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shells; cover with remaining Cool Whip.

title: baby reuben appetizer sandwiches
directions: Put thin slices of corned beef, sauerkraut and Swiss cheese between slices of cocktail rye bread.
Brush the outside of these tiny sandwiches with melted butter and toast on a griddle until lightly browned on both sides and the cheese is melted and serve piping hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco and butter until very fluffy.
Cream with sugar. Add eggs, 2 at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Alternate flour mixture with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 30 minutes at 325° and then bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel, dice and cook potatoes until done.
Dice green pepper, onion, pickles and boiled eggs.
In large bowl, mix all together, except potatoes, leaving those until cooled.
When potatoes have cooled to lukewarm, mix all together and serve.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix and drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.
Cool and store.
Excellent with raspberry or blackberry tea.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, sugars, egg and vanilla in large bowl.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Blend in 1 tablespoon water.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by level spoonful 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 1 minute. Remove from sheets and let cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix with sandwich spread.

title: lemon chicken(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split chicken breasts.
Place each half chicken breast in 12-inch piece of foil.
Salt both sides of breasts.
Sprinkle each breast evenly with tarragon.
Form envelope with foil.
Squeeze lemon on each chicken breast.
Seal foil. Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serves 6 with 110 calories and 2 low-fat meat.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: In a bowl, place softened cream cheese.
Gradually stir in drained crushed pineapple, pecans, green pepper, green onion and seasoned salt.
Mix until blended well.
Cover and chill for several hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: german cabbage
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt the oleo.
Add onion and brown. Remove onion. Add other ingredients.
Mix and let cabbage wilt. Add onion back in.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: beefaroni
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef; drain and pour over macaroni.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Top with cheese.
Brown in oven.

title: aunt phyllis's peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat sugars and milk until it comes to a rolling boil.
Cook until a soft ball is formed when dropped into a glass of cold water (approximately 10 minutes).
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and marshmallow fluff.
Beat until smooth.
Put into a 9x13 pan.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: Cut steak into pieces long enough to roll.
Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 cup stuffing in center.
Roll pinwheel fashion.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in butter; add soup mix.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.
Thicken with flour.

title: garden chicken casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring broth and 1/3 cup white wine to a boil. Add contents of rice package; cover and simmer over low heat 25 to 30 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a Dutch oven, saute onion, carrots and green pepper in butter until soft, about 5 minutes. Add rice, chicken and mushrooms, mixing well.
Place cream cheese, American cheese and milk in a saucepan; melt over medium heat, stirring until smooth. Add to Dutch oven with remaining wine, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Top with Parmesan and almonds. Cover and bake 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until bubbly.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and set aside.
Combine eggs, onion, soup, butter and mayonnaise.
Place a layer of broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Add a layer of cheese.
Pour a small amount of sauce on top.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with 1/2 package of stuffing mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
You may use flavored buttered crumbs as a topping in place of herb stuffing.

title: texas dirt cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar; cream well and set aside.
Blend instant pudding and 3 1/2 cup of milk in another bowl.
Now combine both mixtures.
Fold in Cool Whip. Crush the Oreo cookies.
Line a 9-inch flowerpot with plastic wrap. Layer the mixtures in pot, ending with Oreos.
Place washable artificial flowers in pot and add gummy worms as desired.
Serve with a small spade.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Rub meat well with mixture.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Brush with Mop Sauce.
Bake 4 additional hours, mopping with sauce at least once per hour.

title: iced fruit tea
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil.
Steep tea bags for 10 minutes and pour into gallon container.
Add last 2 ingredients to container and fill with water.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use enough mayonnaise to coat. Chill and serve.

title: easy but great punch
directions: Soften sherbet and add pineapple juice and 7-Up.

title: angel bites
directions: Cut bananas into bite sized pieces.
Dip in lemon juice and roll in toasted coconut.
Pile on a serving dish.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate & margarine over low heat.
Beat eggs with fork until fluffy, add sugar and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder, & salt.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in greased 9x10 pan at 350° for 20-25 min.

title: peanut butter cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the crumbs, margarine and granulated sugar; press onto bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes and cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and 2 cups cracker crumbs and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: poppin' fresh barbecups
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add sauce, sugar and onion. Place biscuits in ungreased muffin pan. Make hole in center of each biscuit. Spoon meat into biscuits. Bake at 400° until brown. Sprinkle on cheese.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; mix well. Add 1/2 cup of milk and stir until sugar and cornstarch are dissolved.
Stir in remaining milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine and butterscotch extract.
Chill about 3 hours, then ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Boil with onion and bell pepper.
To this broth and chicken, add Ro-Tel tomatoes with green chilies. Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and poultry seasoning to suit your personal taste.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add all ingredients and heat.
Eat it warm.

title: piquant grilled chicken
directions: Trim off and discard visible fat from thighs.
In a bowl combine lemon juice and zest, oil, paprika, oregano, onion powder, water, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, cover and marinate refrigerated for at least 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Remove from marinade and grill or broil 6 to 8 inches from heat source until cooked through, 10 to 15 minutes per side.

title: girdle busters
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs over ingredients.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 45 minutes until browned.
Cool completely.

title: banana muffins
directions: Blend shortening, eggs and sugar; add flour, salt, baking powder, soda and salt alternately with milk.
Add nuts and bake in 350° oven until brown.
Muffins usually take 20 minutes.

title: onion-garlic butter
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, beating until well blended.
Cover; chill until serving time, at least 2 hours.

title: pot pie
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Knead in oleo.
Add water slowly. Mix together to make dough.
Divide into quarters.
Take each quarter and roll out thin.
Cut into squares and add to your broth.

title: french bread fairly fast(makes 8 loaves.)
directions: Mix.
Knead.
Put in large greased bowl in warm spot.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Punch down, shape into long loaves; put on greased cookie sheets.
Brush loaves with mixture of 3 beaten egg whites and 3 tsp. water for crust or pan of hot water on lowest rack of oven.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400°.
Make sure to knead to very stiff dough.

title: nutritious pecan fudge
directions: Mash the cooked, drained beans thoroughly.
They will measure 1 cup when mashed.
In a bowl, cream the butter until light.
Beat in the unsweetened cocoa and vanilla (try with black walnut flavoring).
Gradually blend in the confectioners sugar, then the mashed beans, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in the chopped pecans.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Dice the eggs and mix all the ingredients together.
It's great on sandwiches, crackers or just by itself.
Cool and refreshing for the hot summer heat.

title: country noodles
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Cook noodles, based on package directions; drain.
Mix all remaining ingredients (except Parmesan) in large bowl.
Add noodles and bacon; toss until well mixed.
Turn into deep 3 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until heated through.
Remove cover; sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Broil until golden brown.
Serve with extra Parmesan and also extra sour cream (if you wish).

title: apple custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add 1 cup sugar, lemon juice and vanilla. Add apples, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Pour melted butter over top.
Mix cinnamon and 3 teaspoons sugar together, then sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until custard sets.

title: cauliflower-radish salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and cut up.
Wash radishes and slice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill. Will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: shrimp creole(serves 6)
directions: Cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add water, if necessary.
Stir in shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 to 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Serve over rice.

title: charlie's chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour over chicken.
Marinate at least overnight; I marinate my chicken for 3 days!

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiled water.
Allow to congeal.
Add apples, pineapple, cranberry sauce and orange juice.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Put in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: christmas-cinnamon punch
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in boiler.
Add remains.
Stir well. Can be served warm or cold.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: can-do brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crockpot.
Cook on Hi for 1 hour, then turn to Low and cook at least 3 hours.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until they peak. Cook sugar, Karo and water to hard-ball stage or spins 6 to 8-inch thread when poured from spoon. While mixing, pour slowly over STIFFLY beaten egg whites. Stir until it holds a shape when dropped onto wax paper.

title: manhattan meat balls
directions: Mix beef, breadcrumbs, onion, eggs parsley and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls and brown in frying pan.
Or bake until cooked through.

title: veal scallopini marsala
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter. Add juice of 2 lemons and brown sauce. Set aside.

title: yeast buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water with maragrine, combine flour and sugar with yeast water.
Mix and knead until smooth, use more water if needed.
Roll out, cut.
Place in a greased pan. Allow to rise 4 hours with a covered towel in a warm place.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: white cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and water alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in moderate oven. Cover with favorite icing.

title: dressing for diced cucumbers
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour over diced cucumbers.

title: irene's kielbasa soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven or soup kettle. Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Stir often.
Serve piping hot.

title: slushy punch
directions: Stir together sugar and 2 3/4 cups water until sugar dissolves.
In a blender container, combine bananas, half of the pineapple juice and the orange juice concentrate.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Add to mixture.
Stir in remaining pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Freeze for several hours or until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter and mix.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture, mixing thoroughly.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Combine all vegetables with soup, sour cream and cheese in a greased baking dish.
Melt margarine in skillet and add crushed crackers and almonds to coat them. Put cracker mixture on top of vegetables.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Heat milk (scald); set aside.
Mix 1/2 cup warm water and yeast with 1 teaspoon of sugar; set aside.
Mix milk and shortening until shortening softens and melts, then add sugar and beaten eggs.
Sift 3 cups flour and salt; add to mixture.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Add remaining flour until dough is okay to knead.
Knead until dough is not sticky, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Place in large, greased bowl; turn dough over.
Cover with lid or towel.
Don't put it near a draft.
Let raise until dough doubles.
(You can let raise until dough doubles again if you need the time.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Heat oven to warm setting. Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper. In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Brown meat in batches, about 1 minute per side.
Transfer to a platter and place in oven. Melt butter in skillet; add onion and cook 3 minutes until softened.
Add mushrooms. Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mushroom liquid evaporates.
Add wine; cook 5 minutes. Stir in beef broth and cook 10 minutes, until mushrooms are coated with a thick sauce.

title: quick yeast german plum cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Open the tube of dough.
Press half of dough into pan (4 flat triangles).
Press remaining dough evenly over first layer.
Place plum quarters in rolls on dough, cut side up.
Press into dough slightly.
Blend with fingers or pastry blender the sugar, butter, flour and cinnamon.
Sprinkle this mixture on top of plums.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: better bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine first five ingredients; set aside.
Mix bran with milk until bran is moistened; let stand 5 minutes.
Add egg and oil, beating until blended.
Add flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Do not overmix.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, hot water, shortening, salt, cinnamon, cloves, raisins and boil for 3 mins. Cool the ingredients before you add the flour and baking soda. Pour into a greased 9x13in. pan or 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 mins. to an hour.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and shortening with an electric mixer.
Add egg and milk.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Gently fold in the berries and pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch square baking dish.

title: homemade chicken stir-fry
directions: Flatten breasts or use boneless.
Place in baking dish. Combine teriyaki, ginger and garlic.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate for 30 minutes.
Dredge meat until coated with cornstarch.
Add 1/2 of oil; heat until hot.
Stir-fry chicken until brown.
Add remaining oil until hot.
Stir-fry vegetables 1 minute.
Add seasoning packet and broth. Cook 2 minutes.

title: almond tea
directions: Boil 2 cups water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Make tea with remaining 3 cups water and tea bag.
Combine tea and sugar water; add remaining ingredients.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel and cook eggplant; drain and let cool.
Mix eggs and crackers to thick consistency.
Pat into desired cakes and fry in Crisco or Wesson oil for 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, 1 tablespoon of lemon juice and the ginger.
Pour over chicken, stirring to coat. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, honey and 1 tablespoon water.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and egg.
Mix dry ingredients; add alternately with fluids.
Last, fold in drained apricots and nuts.
Spray 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with Pam.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand overnight for easier slicing.

title: orange-tapioca dessert
directions: Serves 8 to 10.

title: sour cream chili bake
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, taco seasoning mix and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Sprinkle 2 1/2 cups corn chips in bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with chili.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread sour cream over chili.
Top with remaining chips and cheese.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french-fried pepper rings
directions: Wash peppers; remove stems, seeds and fleshy ribs.
Cut into 1/4-inch rings.
Heat oil, 1-inch, to 375° in large saucepan or French fryer.
Beat remaining ingredients with rotary beater until smooth. Dip each ring into batter, letting excess drip into bowl. Fry a few at a time in hot oil for about 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: italian plank potatoes(for 2)
directions: Cut potatoes in planks.
Spread tinfoil with butter.
Lay potatoes on foil and sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Cover with more tinfoil and crimp edges.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: claudia's czechoslovakian cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar.
Add yolks, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour, then nuts.
Divide dough in half. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Pat one half of the dough into bottom of pan.
Spread jam over dough.
Take small pieces of second half of dough; pat thin and lay over jam.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: champagne punch
directions: Make up syrup from sugar (dissolve in a small amount of hot water), Curacao and Triple Sec.
Chill.
Pour all ingredients over ice.
Serves 24 people, 4 drinks each.

title: party pink punch
directions: Mix together.
Just before serving, add 1 bottle ginger ale.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix together and pour some in a flat pan (dishpan).
Use a wire hoop (coat hanger).
Make a 6-inch circle.
Leave handle on.
Dip in bubble mixture.
Makes very large bubbles.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs a little in a bowl.
Mix well with remaining ingredients.
Use either a tube pan or a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate fruit balls
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into balls. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store lightly covered in refrigerator.
Flavor improves in 24 hours.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: ripe tomato chow chow
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions, pepper and salt; let stand about 2 hours.
Put mixture in cloth sack, let drain overnight.
Combine tomato mixture with sugar, vinegar and allspice; boil for 2 minutes.
Pack it into hot pint jars.

title: easy as summer pie
directions: Combine lemonade concentrate and Eagle Brand milk, stirring until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Garnish with lemon twist and mint leaves.
Refrigerate until firm (at least 2 hours).

title: spicy winter tea mix
directions: Combine in a bowl or storage jar. Mix with cream cheese or butter for a tasty spread. Mix together and store in an airtight glass container out of heat and light.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the nuts and parsley.
Make into a ball.
Roll in nuts and parsley to cover the ball and chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter, margarine and sugars.
Add the liquids.
Sift dry ingredients together; mix slowly into creamed mixture.
Refrigerate until cool.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in plain sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending until smooth.
Pour into 2 greased and floured round pans.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes. Frost with white or cream cheese frosting.

title: baked beans(in electric roaster-makes large quantity)
directions: Cook at 325° to 350° in oven or at 300° in electric roaster.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli flowers in a cup of water.
Grate onion and saute in butter.
Slowly add in cream of mushroom soup, adding the milk and seasonings (salt, pepper, garlic and Tony's).
Bring to a slow boil, adding in Cheddar cheese, stirring often.
Let come to a rolling boil.
Add broccoli.
Cut heat back; cover with a lid, cooking for 10 minutes.
Let stand another 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into a ball.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour and milk.
Melt margarine in a deep baking dish.
Pour batter over margarine.
Spoon fruit over batter; do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Mix with all other ingredients. Pour into a round baking dish; bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all together and chill one hour.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Put softened ice cream in a large mixing bowl.
Add peanut butter and mix with electric mixer at low speed.
When blended thoroughly, place in chocolate pie crust.
Warm fudge topping in microwave for 35 seconds and drizzle on top of pie in a ribbon pattern.
Chill in freezer for one hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it begins to boil.
Add peanuts.
Cook until peanuts are parched.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: fantastic fruit dessert
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with dry cake mix.
Sprinkle on the nuts and crushed cornflakes.
Drizzle the margarine evenly over the top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: nova scotia fish chowder
directions: Cut fish into bite size chunks.
Saute the salt pork until it is a delicate brown.
Save the scraps for garnish.
Saute the onion until tender.
Add the potatoes and water and simmer until the potatoes are just cooked, then add the fish and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine the remaining ingredients and heat, but don't boil.
Add this to the fish mixture and serve piping hot, garnished with the pork scraps.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda, cream of tartar. In large mixing bowl, mix all the other ingredients. Add the flour mixture.
Refrigerate for two hours (store in refrigerator in between making cookies).

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper together. Drain. Add basil, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, tomato paste and water. Mix well. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In a heavy skillet over medium high heat, cook bacon, onion and okra until lightly browned.
Coarsely chop tomatoes and add to okra mixture, along with juice.
Add seasonings, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until okra is tender.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: kool kokonut dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and put it in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
This is the crust and first layer.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
At same time, brown 1/2 cup coconut.
Mix 1/2 carton Cool Whip with powdered sugar and cream cheese; this is second layer and should be poured over cooled crust.
Cook pudding in milk and cool.
Pour over second layer.
Add other half of Cool Whip and sprinkle with browned coconut.
This is the fourth layer. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Watch coconut carefully, it browns quickly.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Place on bottom of greased baking dish. Cover with pieces of cooked chicken. Combine soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: quick and easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread slices into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cut link sausages into slices and layer over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper and pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
The cheese will rise to the top during baking.
Serves 6 to 8 and can be prepared the night before and put in refrigerator. Recipe can be doubled easily.

title: buttermilk pecan  pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle chopped pecans in unbaked pie crust.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour in small amounts and beat.
Add vanilla, salt and buttermilk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in crust.
Bake 1 hour.

title: taffy-apple salad
directions: In saucepan, combine juice, egg, sugar, flour and vinegar. Cook until thick and clear looking.
Cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Prepare jello
as
directed.
Set
aside.
Stir
strawberries in
jello.
Mix bananas, nuts and pineapple; fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into dish and let set until thick. Spread
the sour cream over set mixture as icing for cake.
Pour rest of strawberry on and set in refrigerator.

title: swiss pie
directions: Fresh and canned fruits and fresh vegetables make tempting snacks by themselves.
But don't stop there.
Think of other ways to use fruits and vegetables, such as the following:

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain and cool.
In large bowl mix potatoes, pepper, onion, mustard and mayonnaise.
Add 3 eggs and garlic powder; mix again well.
Garnish with egg and paprika.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix until creamy the cake mix, eggs, water and Dream Whip. Spread rhubarb and sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cake will crack on top.

title: simply elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut steak in thin strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil using low heat.
Add onion.
Saute until tender-crisp.
Blend soup, sherry, liquid from mushrooms and salt.
Simmer 1 hour. Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: lora jean's baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Add the tomato soup, water and chili powder. Simmer for 30 minutes. Pour on top of 7 ounces broken, dry spaghetti. Add cheeses. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix butter and lard, sugar, egg and molasses until smooth.
Add dry ingredients, blending well.
Add hot water and beat until smooth.
Bake in a shallow pan at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: gladys davis coconut pie
directions: Put milk and 1/2 cup sugar in double boiler and cook.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Add this and egg yolks to milk and cook until thick.
Beat egg whites with approximately 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Put on top of pie and cover with coconut.
Bake at 325° until coconut begins to brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda; mix well.
Pour over popcorn and stir until well coated.
Pour into two greased 13x9x2 inch baking pans.
Bake, uncovered, at 250 degrees for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight containers or plastic bags.

title: beef casserole
directions: Dice onions; boil for 5 minutes.
Leave in water.
Cook ground beef; drain.
Peel potatoes; slice in thin slices.
Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Alternate potatoes and beef, starting with potatoes and ending with beef.
Salt and pepper meat.
Add soup to onion and water; simmer until thick.
Pour over potatoes and beef.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: jellied fruit compote
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a bowl.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Fold in pineapple chunks, orange segments, grapefruit and cherries.
Pour into 2-quart crystal serving bowl.
Chill until set.
Decorate with whipped cream, orange segments and cherries just before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: large sugar cookies
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk; drop by tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet (6 cookies to sheet).
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: lemon raisin cookies
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together and add the next 4 ingredients.
Add raisins.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, making a crisscross pattern.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: potatoes a l'alsacienne
directions: Melt the butter in a very large sauce pan. Add cabbage, onions, salt and pepper. Do not discard juice left in sauce pan. Cook until wilted. Into a 3 quart casserole place cabbage, onions, potatoes and cheese. Add 2 tablespoons butter to the juices left in the sauce pan and melt over low heat. Stir in flour. Slowly add broth and Vermouth, stirring. Continue stirring until sauce bubbles and thickens. When sauce is ready, pour over casserole and sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes, or until golden.

title: chocolate mint mousse
directions: Cream the margarine.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Blend in chocolate, then eggs one at a time.
Add extracts, then blend in Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours.
Top with chocolate curls or crushed peppermint candy.

title: armadillo eggs no. 2
directions: Spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Halve the jalapenos and seed. Salt and pepper the hamburger meat.
Stuff the peppers with the cream cheese on the hamburger meat.
Sausage may also be used. Wrap the stuffed peppers with the bacon strips.
Bake at 350° until browned, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie and topping
directions: Put in double boiler.
Stir constantly until thick then put 1/2 stick butter.
Put in baked pie shell, then put topping on and brown.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Cover bottom of crust with coconut.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
