Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken lasagna bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine soup, broth and salt; stir until smooth.
Combine cream cheese and the next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add onion.
Layer half of noodles and cream cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Add butter and bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: beef internationale
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Add onions, green peppers and water. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, adding more water, if necessary. Add soup, combined with Miracle Whip and mushrooms.
Season to taste.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles, sprinkled with paprika.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Mix in a large glass or Tupperware (2 to 4 cups) measuring cup the margarine, brown sugar, cinnamon, syrup and pecans. Pour 1/4 of mixture in bottom of a Bundt pan. Put biscuits on sides inside Bundt pan. Pour remaining mixture over biscuits. Bake in a 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes. Makes 16.

title: whoopie pies
directions: In mixing bowl beat together 1/2 cup shortening and sugar on high speed of electric mixer until fluffy.
Add the egg and egg yolk.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt; set aside.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water; cool slightly.
Add flour mixture alternately with soda mixture and buttermilk to creamed mixture. Blend until well mixed.
Drop batter by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool cookies on wire rack while preparing filling.

title: stuffed baked peppers
directions: Rinse and quarter the green peppers.
Remove the inside seeds. Add to a large bowl the ground beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and egg.
Add 1/2 can of the tomato soup, undiluted.
Mix well. Place the peppers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the mixture to each pepper (heap up a little high).
Mix 1/2 can of water (from the soup can) to the 1/2 can tomato juice.
Mix well and add to the tops of each green pepper.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, flour or cornstarch and water in top of double boiler.
Cook until thick and smooth, stirring occasionally.
Just before removing from heat, stir in butter and lemon extract.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until completely cooled.
May be topped with whipped cream.

title: lemon butter sauce
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter; stir
in ReaLemon juice and salt.
Serve with seafood, fish or vegetables.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Can be made into a roll and rolled in an additional cup of chopped pecans.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Put nuts in quart jar with screw on cap.
(You may use walnuts, pecans or dry-roasted mixed nuts or cashews.)
Add sugar and spices.
Shake well to coat nuts.
Spiced nuts are a sure-to-please gift.
Can be packed in a glass container with nuts glued on top.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in baking dish.
Mix together: 1 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour into baking dish with butter.
Ppour peaches, with syrup over above mixture.
Sprinkle one cup of sugar evenly over top.

title: summer pecan pie
directions: Crush crackers.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and nuts.
Beat egg whites. Add 1/2 cup sugar with vanilla.
Fold into mixture.
Spoon into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: tropical sorbet smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 2.
Delicious.

title: maple graham crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar with mixer until creamy.
Then beat in egg and maple flavoring. Add graham cracker crumbs and flour, blending thoroughly.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 19 to 23 dozen.

title: shake 'n bake chicken
directions: Mix and blend all ingredients.
Roll chicken or pork chops in beaten egg, then in this mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet in 3 tablespoons of oil.

title: 2 buttermilk pies
directions: Have butter soft; add sugar and cream.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before serving.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Slice lettuce across and up and down to shred. Place in bottom of large bowl. Add a layer each of celery, green pepper, spanish onion and peas. Cover with a 1/4 inch layer of mayonnaise. Sprinkle with sugar. Cover with generous layer of parmesan and bacos. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Toss right before serving.

title: m-m-m good fruit cake
directions: Add 1 cup water to the mincemeat; boil for 3 minutes, then cool.
Set aside.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add cool mincemeat; mix well together. Blend eggs.
Add flour, alternately with soup.
Mix until smooth. Mix in nuts.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes, or until done.
Cool.
Cover with white icing, or dribble with icing and decorate with nuts and cherries.

title: white jello
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add milk and vanilla; set aside.
Dissolve gelatine in hot water; add cold water.
Cool.

title: slimmed strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Add pineapple and juice, mashed bananas and sour cream.
Mix and pour into 13x9x2-inch dish or mold.
Refrigerate until set and ready to serve.

title: guacamole ring
directions: Then mix 2 cups of Miracle Whip with 2 tablespoons of sugar. Spread on top of layers in dish.
Then sprinkle one package of shredded Cheddar cheese on top of that.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Finely chop the onion, carrots and celery.
Melt the butter in a stockpot.
Add the chopped onions, carrots and celery.
Saut until the onions are clear and limp on medium heat (about 7 to 8 minutes).
Season the mixture with basil and black and red pepper while it cooks.
You will need to stir the mixture while it is cooking.
Gradually add the flour, stirring constantly.
You want it to be pasty; add a little more flour if needed.
Add the water and chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Cook the mixture on medium while you cube the potatoes.
Add the potatoes and cook on medium for about 15 minutes.
Make sure you stir to keep from sticking.
Add the whipping cream and reduce heat to low for about another 10 minutes. Serve with Cheddar cheese on top.

title: baked honey tomatoes
directions: I use less pepper and tarragon.

title: pickled jalapeno mix
directions: Simmer the carrots for 2 minutes.
Add onions and jalapenos. Simmer for 3 minutes, until vegetables are hot.
Drain.
Make a brine by mixing the vinegar, oil, water, salt, oregano and turmeric.
Bring to a boil.
Place 1 clove garlic in hot pint canning jar.
Fill with hot vegetables.
Seal with canning lids immediately and process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes.

title: light buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened (batter may be lumpy).
Bake on hot griddle.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: shrimp, pea and mushroom stir-fry
directions: Blend cornstarch, salt, sugar, ginger, chicken broth, soy sauce and garlic.
Heat wok or large skillet.
Add oil and mushrooms, fry 1 minute.
Add peas and onion, fry 2 minutes.
Add shrimp, cook until pink.
Add chicken broth mixture and cook until thick.
Serve with hot cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sawmill pie
directions: Mix all by hand; pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325° or until glossy.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour wings
directions: Marinate 24 wings overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in marinated sauce.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Prepare pasta as package directs; drain.
Keep warm. Meanwhile, drain clams, reserving liquid.
Lightly brown garlic in the butter.
Add clam liquid; bring to boil.
Add clams, parsley, sherry, pepper and salt to taste.
Cook until hot.
Toss sauce with pasta.
Serves 4.

title: old style scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil a 2-quart casserole lightly. Heat oil in medium saucepan on medium-high heat. Add onion. Cook and stir until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and 1/8 teaspoon paprika. Blend in milk. Cook and stir on medium-high heat until sauce comes to a boil and is thickened.
Layer 1/3 of the potatoes on bottom of casserole. Top with 1/3 of the sauce.
Repeat twice. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover. Bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Serves 8.

title: grape and sour cream salad
directions: Wash and stem the grapes.
Pat dry.
Blend the softened cream cheese with the sour
cream;
add the sugar and vanilla. Mix with the grapes.
Put
it
in
a
flat serving dish.
When ready to serve, sprinkle brown sugar over top.

title: pecan pies
directions: Pour into 2 pie shells and bake very slowly.

title: lemon coconut cookies
directions: Mix everything together.
Spoon a teaspoon of dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° just until edges of cookie turn brown. Don't overbake.

title: pecan log
directions: Mix together marshmallow cream, sugar and flavoring.
Makes stiff dough.
Divide into 5 pieces and roll into 5-inch long rolls.
Put in refrigerator and freeze (or until stiff and firm).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Wash and peel eggplants.
Cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Dip into egg, then into flour.
Brown on both sides in oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Set aside.
Melt velveeta.
Add
tomatoes and cumin.
Mix until creamy.
In a 9 x 11 inch dish, layer eggplant and velveeta mixture until all is used.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Dissolve flour in milk.
Blend to a smooth paste.
Cook until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Gradually add butter and sugar, beating with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.

title: oatmeal - cinammon cookies
directions: Heat oven 375°.
Mix sugar, margarine, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix everything together and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie pans. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: party bean dip
directions: Clean and soak beans overnight or "cook all day!"
If beans are soaked, they only take about 1 hour to soften.
Test with a fork.
If beans aren't soaked, they will take 2 to 3 hours or until done.
Cook on high and bring to a boil, turn down to medium or at a slow rolling boil until done.
Strain water out of beans and then before putting back in pan, cook meat and chop up.
Fry a cup or two of beans in a little meat grease, then add the rest of the beans and mash with potato masher.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Enjoy!
Eat with chips or tortilla.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; chill.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: make ahead 3-bean salad
directions: Drain the 3 cans of beans and mix together well in a large bowl.
Add chopped peppers and onions.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti noodles until tender; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Fill manicotti. Arrange manicotti in shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).

title: pan-fried fish
directions: Season fish with salt and peppers, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add mustard; mix well.
Heat a black iron skillet and melt butter and olive oil together.
Roll fish in fish fry and fry. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: beer basted chicken legs
directions: Mix everything but the chicken in a small bowl.
Place chicken, skin side up, on prepared grill, about 8 inches from heat.
Grill, turning every 10 minutes for about 35 minutes. Brush with sauce, grill, turning and basting chicken every 5 minutes for about 20 minutes or more, until chicken is fork tender.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
With electric mixer, beat until smooth.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread salsa over cheese; sprinkle the onion, pepper, tomatoes and lettuce on top.
Finish with a layer of Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips (2 bags).

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: potato cheese puff dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a baking dish sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until blade of knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: three cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll 1 package of crescent rolls. Roll out and pinch seams together.
Spread softened cream cheese over crescent rolls.
Next sprinkle with Monterey Jack, then Cheddar.
Lay out 2nd package of crescent rolls.
Pinch seams together.
Place over top of bottom crust and cheeses.
Seal edges with sealing wheel or knife.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Slit top. Bake about 25 minutes.
Serve warm with your favorite crackers or apple slices.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix both in large bowl.
Stir thoroughly to make sura all dry parts of mix are incorporated.
Chill several hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: easy chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Debone chicken.
Cook until tender.
Combine and add 1/2 cup water to 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Prepare dressing according to directions, using 2 cups of water per package.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam, place chicken on bottom, stuffing on next and soup on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans or 3 (8 1/2 x 4 1/4 x 2 1/2) pans. In a large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy; stir in eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and spices. Stir in nuts and raisins. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 70 minutes.

title: debbie's salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Mix and chill.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Combine butter and honey in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread to sides of pan, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Combine eggs, juice and salt in shallow bowl; mix well.
Dip bread one at a time into egg mixture, coating well; let drain and arrange on top of honey mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Invert toast to serve.
Serve with additional honey.

title: banana oatmeal cake topping
directions: Mix margarine, milk and sugar.
Add coconut.
Ice cake.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and shortening; add all ingredients, mixing well!
Add 1/2 cup of vanilla wafer crumbs to bottom of tube pan. Pour in cake mix; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: douglas kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut and squeeze dry with hands.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil the water, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over kraut mixture.
Add oil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy cheese dip
directions: Beat at med speed until well blended.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork gently.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine together.
Sift sugar and cocoa until there are no lumps.
Mix sugar mixture into melted butter and cheese.
Blend thoroughly with wooden spoon or hands.
Add nuts and vanilla. Press into 2 (13 x 9-inch) buttered pans.
Let set until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 7 pounds.

title: cinnamon crunch applesauce
directions: Pour applesauce in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine crackers, sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Sprinkle this topping over applesauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until topping browns.
Serve hot or cold with or without cream.

title: best black-eyed pea salad
directions: Place drained black-eyed peas in a large ceramic salad bowl. Mix all liquid ingredients and spices in a separate bowl with a whisk.
Mix onion, parsley, olives and bell pepper in a third bowl. Combine everything in the ceramic bowl; toss gently.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix well and store in freezer for at least 24 hours.
Serve with straws or spoons.
Add an orange slice or cherry.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into pie crust.
Put other half of pie crust on top.
Crimp edges.
Beat egg whites.
Brush on top of crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes. Serve with salad or cole slaw.

title: cream pie
directions: Heat milk.
Mix other ingredients and stir into hot milk. Cook until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger, bacon and onions.
In baking dish, put in the 5 cans of beans, juice and all, plus rest of ingredients.
Mix all and bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Spoon both cans of pie filling over cream mixture.
Chill well before serving!

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring the cornstarch, sugar and water to a boil. Add Jell-O. Boil until it becomes thick.
Cool.
Pour this mixture over strawberries.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Sprinkle garlic seasoning and Parmesan cheese into bread crumbs.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggplant, onion and half the spaghetti sauce in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over this; add remaining spaghetti sauce.
Put Mozzarella cheese over this.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pumpkin or zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add the sugar, oil, pumpkin or zucchini and vanilla and mix lightly, but well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon and add to the egg-pumpkin or zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended; add nuts and pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.
Freezes very well.

title: appetizers
directions: Wrap Waverly crackers with bacon.
Lay on baking sheet; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Broil until bacon is crisp.

title: boyfriend cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine.
Slowly beat in sugars.
Add unbeaten eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in separate bowl flour, soda and oats.
Add to first mixture. Stir in peanuts and chocolate bits; mix well.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: johnnycake(my mother's recipe)
directions: Pour melted butter over ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° until done.
My mother melted the butter in the pan she was going to bake the Johnnycake in.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Boil the oleo, sugar and Pet milk until hard ball forms in water. Take off and add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and pecans.
Pour on slightly greased cookie sheets or plates.

title: crab or shrimp mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3 tablespoons cold water; add to heated mushroom soup.
Mash cream cheese until creamy, add mayonnaise, celery, onions, crab (shrimp) and soup mixes.
Pour into decorative mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and serve with crackers. Serves 12 to 16.

title: prize muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend with pastry cutter until smooth. Add eggs; mix.
Add flour; mix.
Add pecans.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Makes 12.
Great for mini muffins too!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until well mixed.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
No mixer!
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baltimore crab cakes
directions: Mix crab meat, salt, dry mustard, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, egg, mayonnaise and parsley.
Press mixture together into 8 small cakes.
Just before serving, dip cakes into egg, then into crumbs/seasonings.
Fry cakes rapidly (in oil) over high heat until delicately brown.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Cook until it strikes a rolling boil; then boil for 2 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add oats and 2 heaping tablespoons of peanut butter. Mix, then drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Mix together
the sugars, butter and eggs. Add the rest of the
ingredients,
mixing thoroughly.
Shape into one-inch balls and place
on
cookie
sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until done.

title: rice pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, combine rice and 2 cups milk.
Cook, stirring occasionally, over boiling water until rice is tender. Stir in butter.
Beat eggs; blend in sugar, vanilla, salt and remaining milk.
Stir into the hot rice.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix well. Serve with vegetables or crackers. The flavor blends well if mixed the day before.

title: real pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add flour and eggs alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Flavor with vanilla.
Bake in tube pan or 2 loaves at 275° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: roberta's baked salami
directions: Score salami (crisscross) on top.
Bake in 325° oven for about 2 hours.
Serve on small cocktail rye bread and pumpernickel bread.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Put in pan to jell.
Cook sugar, pineapple juice, flour and egg until thick. Remove and add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour over Jell-O.

title: pineapple royal
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar together.
Line a flat bottomed pan with waxed paper (13 x 13-inch pan).
Take half the wafer crumbs and sprinkle in pan.
Spread with butter/sugar mixture. Add the drained pineapple, then top with a layer of whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Scatter the pecan halves over top and then cover with the rest of wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Spread mixture on small French bread rounds.
Broil until hot and bubbly.
Makes 125.

title: garden chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, zucchini, carrot, onion and parsley in large serving bowl.
Combine mayonnaise dressing, sour cream, celery salt and pepper in small bowl.
Add to chicken mixture.
Mix well. Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: curried cheese nut sandwiches
directions: Mix celery, peanuts, chives, cheese, seasonings and mayonnaise.
Stuff breads with the mixture.
Sandwiches may be eaten cold with the tomatoes or wrapped in foil and heated.
To heat, place on oven rack and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Open pockets; add tomatoes and enjoy.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise with mixer until smooth. Heat soup and gelatine until warm.
Flake shrimp and add to cream cheese; blend well.
Add to soup mixture.
Put in 1 1/2-quart Tupperware mold and refrigerate until firm.
(Can be made a couple days before serving.)

title: stromboli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 12 to 14-inch pizza pan.
Roll out dough to a 12 to 14-inch circle.
On half the dough, place grated cheese, ham, pepperoni and other pizza toppings you choose.
Carefully fold the other half of the dough over filling half.
Use a fork and press edges together to seal tightly.
Slide the stromboli away from the edge of the pan.
Cut 3 slits in the top half.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until a golden brown.
Slice and serve with heated spaghetti sauce. Enjoy!!!

title: cheeseburger loaves
directions: Crush the corn flakes and put in a large bowl. Add the egg, tomatoes, salt and pepper and beat well. Add the ground beef and mix until combined.
Shape into loaves and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes. Remove and top with the cheese. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put papers into tartlet pans.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Drop rounded teaspoonful into each.
Beat cream cheese, egg and sugar until well blended.
Fill each pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Chill thoroughly.
When ready to serve, top with cherry.
Can be frozen up to 3 months without cherry.

title: buttery beets
directions: On medium grater grate beets; arrange in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt, garlic salt, and pepper; dot with butter.
Simmer, covered, 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Pass vinegar or lemon wedges at table.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: Brown beef and sausage with onion and oregano.
Drain.
Add soups and water.
Cook noodles and combine with meat mixture. Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.
Top with cheese.
Bake until melted.

title: white cake with pears
directions: Put pears and juice in a small bowl.
Cut pears into small pieces and mash up in the juice.
Put the cake mix in a large bowl of the electric mixer.
Add oil, egg whites and pears with juice. Blend and mix until moistened.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: harvest drink
directions: Mix the ingredients together in the exact order given and serve on hot days.
Yields one gallon.

title: southwestern grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Spread bread slices with cottage cheese (about 1/4 cup each). Sprinkle on green chilies.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar over chilies. Top with second slice bread.
Butter outside of bread slices and grill on both sides until brown.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Place in bottom of casserole dish. Mix in mayo (or sour cream) with soup; pour over chicken.
Melt butter in separate bowl.
Crumble crackers and mix with butter. Put on top of soup mixture and add poppy seed on top.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles in the middle.

title: frozen cheese salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with salt, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Then add pineapple, sliced bananas, nuts and cherries.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into freezing tray or individual molds.
When frozen, serve on crisp lettuce leaf.
Garnish with fresh fruit (strawberries, peaches) if you care to.

title: special occasion mints
directions: Mix together and knead sugar and cheese.
Add extract and food coloring (to reach desired color) or just extract if you prefer creme-color mints.
Use candy-mint molds to shape.
Freeze or refrigerate until time to use.

title: janet's chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice in medium baking dish.
Combine the cream of celery and cream of chicken together; pour over rice.
Place the 4 skinless chicken breasts on top of the other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine in a saucepan sugar and cocoa; add butter and milk. Stirring constantly, boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop immediately onto waxed paper to cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 2 cups strawberries with a pastry blender.
Put in a saucepan with cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook until thickens.
Stir in remaining 2 cups strawberries, halved.
Add small amount of red coloring.
Put in a baked pie shell.
Chill; cover with Cool Whip.

title: cracker party mix
directions: Stir oil over crackers.
Add dill weed.
Keep stirring. Sprinkle in dressing.
Stir well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir again.
Ready to eat.
Store in covered container.

title: garnete horton's hot spiced tea
directions: Add spices to water and bring to a boil.
Add tea.
Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Strain and pour in teapot. Heat juices and sugar. Add to tea.
Very good on a cold day.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 7 x 11-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Mix the eggs, sugar, salt, lemon juice, baking powder and flour together and pour over the baked mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.
Also cut in squares while hot.
Makes 20 squares.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat eggs whites until stiff.
Add Cream of Tartar.
Crush crackers. Fold crackers, vanilla, sugar and pecans into egg whites.
Bake in a grease pie plate for 30 minutes at 325 degrees. After pie cools, add icing

title: hot mushroom canapes
directions: Cut each slice of bread into quarters; place on cookie sheet and bake at 250° until browned lightly.
Set "toasted" bread aside.
Saute the mushrooms and onion in melted butter; drain.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Combine yeast, sugar, baking powder and shortening with milk. Mix flour to make a stiff dough. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with floured biscuit cutter. Butter top of each biscuit and place one on top of another.
(These are doubled decked biscuits.) Let rise 1 hour.
Place on greased pan and bake at 375° until brown.

title: chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken into strips and roll in flour.
Fry chicken in oil until slightly brown (use enough oil to cover chicken).
In a saucepan, add margarine, garlic salt, bouillon cubes, water and clove.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes and then add chicken strips.
(Do not add oil.)
Cook for an additional 20 minutes.
Remove clove before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except filling and glaze; beat 30 seconds. Spread half of batter in greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over and drop remaining batter by spoonfuls over.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle with a mixture of powdered sugar and milk.
Serve warm or cold.
Can be halved and baked in 9-inch square pan.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Put warm water and dry yeast into small bowl.
Add brown sugar.
Let stand until it bubbles.
Mix well in large bowl:
warm water, shortening, brown sugar, salt, wheat flour and white flour. Let rise for 30 minutes.
(This will be soft.)
Now add 2 more cups white flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Make into loaves.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 medium loaves.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in a covered casserole dish; cook for 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.

title: easy, easy green bean casserole
directions: Stir soup and soy sauce; mix in the rest.
Save some grated Cheddar cheese and some onion rings to sprinkle on top, then bake at 350° in the oven for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Blend sugars, margarine, eggs and peanut butter until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Spread with frosting.

title: buttermilk pecan pancakes
directions: In a bowl, beat the egg yolks and butter. Combine flour, pecans, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to the egg mixture alternately with buttermilk. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter. Pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto a lightly greased hot griddle; turn when bubbles form on top of pancakes. Cook until second side is golden brown. Yield: 16 pancakes.

title: tuna jellied salad
directions: Drain tuna, rinse and drain.
Dissolve jello in water.
Add about 1/4 cup of cold water to the pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and let set until jelled.

title: soldier dish
directions: In a casserole dish, layer all ingredients, beginning with thinly sliced potatoes.
Repeat to top of dish. Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with a green salad and dinner rolls.
A wonderful hot and hearty dish.

title: apple-carrot salad
directions: Combine the apples with grated carrot and minced onion.
Add sour cream; blend in lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Serve on lettuce.

title: taco dip
directions: Press cream cheese into dish.
Heat chili and pour over cream cheese.
Layer other ingredients as listed and to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: chicken tarragon salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, refrigerate and serve on rolls or bread.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese until fluffy. In another bowl, mix bananas, strawberries, pineapple and nuts. Stir in Cool Whip. Mix with cream cheese mixture. Freeze. Cut in squares. This makes a big pan full. Freeze in square pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese, and powdered sugar. Mix together milk, pudding, and Cool Whip.
Add gradually to the cream mixture and mix well.
Spread 1 1/2 inches deep of cookie crumbs in bottom of pan.
Add 1 layer of filling and layer of cookie crumbs.
End with layer of cookie crumbs.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
When ready to serve, add chilled pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Add ice cubes or ice ring.
Makes 100 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first
four ingredients together, then roll ball or log in the 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Toss beef with flour, salt and pepper. Mix in casserole dish with oil. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes. Stir once. Add rest of the ingredients and cover. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together all but Ritz crackers in a baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Ritz crackers and melted margarine, blended well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poor man's breakfast or supper
directions: Cook all these ingredients. Pour off any grease.
Put in flour or cornstarch in 1 large glass of water to thicken.
Cook until thickened.
Put more water if too thick.
Put this over toast or rice.

title: okra pilau
directions: Fry bacon slowly and remove from pan to drain on paper towels. Add okra and onion to bacon grease; saute until tender. Season with salt and pepper. Add water.
Pour mixture over rice in top of steamer. Add crumbled bacon.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, with fork for about 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: veal (or pork) parmesan
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and paprika. Dip meat in beaten egg, then crumb mixture.
Brown on both sides in hot olive oil.
Place slice of Mozzarella cheese after each piece of meat.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Cover, simmer 50 minutes or until meat is done.
Add water, if needed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls in an ungreased pan.
Pinch the edges together.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown. With a mixer, combine the dry dressing mix, cream cheese and Miracle Whip; spread on cooled crust.
Top with a layer of shredded lettuce, then top with various vegetables.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top; slice black olives over top for color.

title: marie's 4-alarm chili
directions: In Dutch oven, cook crumbled sausage, onion and garlic in hot oil until sausage is no longer pink; drain. Add remaining ingredients except Cheddar, sour cream and green onions. Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time. Add milk and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325 degrees and bake for 1 hour more. Can be baked in 11 1/2 x 15 1/2 pan for squares.
Baking time for squares is 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blue cheese log
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Add pineapple cream cheese spread, Blue cheese, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Place mixture onto 1 foot long piece of waxed paper and form into log.
Remove waxed paper and dust log evenly with grated walnuts.
Re-wrap in wax paper and chill thoroughly before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Pour into prepared crust; sprinkle with chopped peanuts and freeze until firm.
Yield:
2 pies.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and corn meal.
Add eggs, butter, buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Cool in pan or wire rack.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars. Add eggs and cream well. Add cooking oil.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.

Form into balls. Dip bottom of glass in granulated sugar and press down on balls of dough until flat but not thin. Bake at 350° until bottom of cookies are lightly brown. Don't let top of cookies brown.

title: black beans and rice salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans and rice.
Mix well.
Fold tomato mixture into beans and rice.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour to blend flavors.
Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.
(Pace picante sauce can be added for extra zip.)

title: apple pie
directions: Put chopped apples in unbaked pie crust.
Beat egg.
Add apple pie spice, flour, salt, sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Pour over chopped apples.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: "great" northern beans
directions: Place beans in casserole dish.
Cut bacon into small pieces and cook until crisp.
Drain.
Reserve small amount of bacon grease.
Saute onion until almost transparent; drain.
Add bacon, onion and sugar to beans.
Mix well.
Heat in 350° oven until heated through.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add lemon juice, pineapple and sugar.
Chill. Prepare 2 packages of the Dream Whip according to package directions.
When gelatin mixture is partially set, combine with Dream Whip and angel food cake, broken into small pieces.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill for several hours, then prepare the other 2 packages of Dream Whip.
Spread over cake; sprinkle coconut over the top.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Add 1/2 cup salad oil and 3/4 cup sugar to sauerkraut and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
When ready to serve, add celery, green pepper and pimento.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix together with jar of salsa.
Add additional seasonings to taste, if needed.
Spread over flour tortillas; roll up like jelly rolls.
Refrigerate overnight or for several hours, until firm.
Slice in cross sections and place on platter for serving.

title: beef rice casserole
directions: Brown beef. Then add green pepper, onion, celery, and rice. Cook until rice is golden. Add soup, salt, pepper and pepper sauce. Heat to a boil; stir well. Pour in 2 qt. casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned raisin pie
directions: In a bowl beat eggs.
Add sour cream.
Stir in raisins, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Place bottom pastry in a pie plate; pour in filling.
Top with a lattice crust.
Bake 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce the heat at 350°.
Bake for about 25 minutes more or until filling is set.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Take pineapple juice and add enough water to make 1 c of liquid.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg until thick. Cool, Dissolve Jello in 1/2 c boiling water; cool slightly.
Add 7-Up, drained pineapple, diced bananas, marshmallows and nuts. Fold in whipping cream.
Pour into large flat serving dish.
Chill until firm.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Beat egg.
Mix in juice from fruit, if any.
Add milk, flour and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: best burger
directions: Mix beef gently with liquid and pat into a plump beef patty. Broil until desired doneness.
Spread catsup on one half of bun and mayonnaise on the other.
Place hamburger on top of catsup and top with tomato, onion and lettuce leaf.
Now hide the pickle chip in the middle.
Top with second half of bun.
Eat while meat is hot and toppings are crisp.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and corn meal together, then add margarine, eggs, milk, vanilla and pecans.
Stir with spoon.
Bake in unbaked pie shells for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: no bake cookie chocolate oatmeal
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in saucepan; bring to a full, rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Beat together.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper on cookie sheets.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt the margarine in a baking dish.
Mix the flour, sugar and milk together; pour in the baking dish, then pour the berries in last.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: sausage, red beans and rice
directions: Saute sausage slices until lightly browned.
Prepare rice. Add beans, corn, pepper and salsa.
Continue cooking until pepper is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: banana nut bread(2 loaves)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients in order. Beat well.
Bake in slow oven (350°) for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: people puppy chow(child-approved)
directions: Melt together first 4 ingredients.
Pour melted ingredients over cereal and coat thoroughly.
(Stir gently while coating or cereal will be crushed.)
Put powdered sugar into paper bag.
Pour chocolate-coated cereal in and shake until thoroughly covered with powdered sugar.
Store in an airtight container.
Does not need refrigeration if used within a short period.
If it is to be kept longer, keep in refrigerator (especially in hot weather), or may be frozen.

title: chicken with sweet potatoes
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Heat oil in large skillet; saute chicken until it is well browned.
Remove chicken from skillet. Add onion and garlic; saute for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add bay leaf, broth and tomatoes.
Mix well and add 3/4 cup water.
Return chicken and sweet potatoes to skillet; simmer, covered, about 40 minutes, until chicken and potatoes are tender.

title: streusel cream cheese pumpkin muffins(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Combine 2 eggs, 2 cups sugar, oil and pumpkin; mix well. Combine flour, pie spice, soda and salt in large bowl; make well in center.
Pour pumpkin mixture into well; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon half of batter into 24 paper-lined muffin cups.
Combine cream cheese, 1 egg and 1 tablespoon sugar; mix well.
Spoon over partially filled muffin cups.
Spoon remaining batter over cream cheese mixture carefully, spreading to edges.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon Pecan Streusel Topping over each muffin.
Bake in a 350° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake to mix well.
Brush both sides of chicken with buttermilk.
Place in bag of crumbs and shake to coat.
Place chicken on broiler pan, which has been sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.
Per Serving:
200 calories; 75 mg. cholesterol; 3 gm. fat; 110 mg. sodium.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Beat egg and add water, vinegar and salt.
Mix thoroughly and add egg mixture to flour mixture; mix as usual.
Form into ball or log and refrigerate.
If you want to freeze, refrigerate several hours, cut into sections and freeze.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar, egg and syrup. Mix flour, soda and salt. Stir together cinnamon and allspice. Put all ingredients in mixing bowl in order given and mix well.
Drop into greased cookie sheet and flatten with a wet fork. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 70 to 80 cookies.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, oil and sugar.
Blend well.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing after each.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine margarine and cheese.
Mix well.
Add flour and pepper and mix, using hands, as it is stiff.
Using star design, press through cookie press onto slightly greased cookie sheets.
Cook at 300° for 30 minutes.
Yields 48 straws.

title: boo's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Boil with a pinch of soda until skins peel by blowing on them.
Drain.
Alternate beans, vegetables and pork, cut into 2-inch squares, in bean pot.
Cover with water and bake in slow oven at least 12 hours.
Add water as necessary to keep moist.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Cool, then serve.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cook eggs in hot boiling water for 10 minutes. When cool, cut eggs in half lengthwise, scoop out yolk with spoon.
In a small bowl, mash yolk with a fork and add remaining ingredients except paprika.
Blend together. Spoon mixture back into egg whites and sprinkle with paprika.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Sprinkle jello over top. Mix well and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Wash tomatoes with stem on.
Put in quart jars.
To each quart jar, add 1 clove garlic, 1 stalk celery, 1 hot pepper and 1 head fresh dill, 1 teaspoon dill weed or 2 tablespoons dill seed. Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to full boil and fill jars to 1/2-inch from top.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing southern style
directions: Mix meal, flour, soda, salt and milk and mix well.
Beat 5 eggs well.
Mix in eggs.
Bake in 450° oven, not too brown.
Boil chicken until tender with lots of water.
When cooked, remove from broth.
Pick from bones.
Mix cornbread with broth (not too soupy).
Add some biscuits or light bread, crumbled into small pieces, but not too many.
Add eggs (beaten) to bread mixture. Mix in onions, celery and chicken.
I add 1 can of cream of chicken soup and 1 can of water, if needed.
Bake at 350° or 450° until lightly browned.
Serve with giblet gravy and cranberry sauce.

title: pasta e. fagioli
directions: Chop onion, celery and garlic and cook in oil until onions are limp.
Add tomato sauce, undrained kidney beans, water and all seasonings.
Cover and cook very slowly for about 30 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly.
Meanwhile, cook the macaroni until tender according to package directions.
Drain.
Just before serving, stir into the bean tomato mixture.
Serves 4.
Sprinkle top with grated Parmesan cheese if you like.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When it starts to congeal add other ingredients.
Be sure to rinse and drain the shrimp first.

title: fruit slush
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into 8 ounce plastic cups.
Cover and freeze 4 hours or until ready to serve.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 to 45 minutes before serving.

title: 5 can chicken casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly.
You can double with 1 chicken if you really have to stretch.

title: maui macadamia macaroons
directions: Place coconut and nuts on a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly toasted, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix frozen peas (do not cook), chopped onion, diced tomatoes, sugar and mayonnaise together.
Top with shredded cheese, then bacon bits.
Serve cold.

title: favorite fruit salad
directions: Reserve juices from pineapple and oranges.
If necessary, add enough water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Mix with pudding and pie filling.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Cool and pour over fruit mixture.
Stir well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in pan to be used in baking bread. Coat pan with melted butter, then add remaining butter to other ingredients. Mix all ingredients well, pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Ritz crackers and margarine.
Put in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch glass).
Cover with Ritz crackers mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Saute celery, onions and garlic in butter. Cook sausage and drain fat. Add remaining ingredients to sausage.
Mix in sauteed onions, celery and garlic.
Place in casserole and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In a trifle bowl, layer:
On bottom, pieces of brownie.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water, corn syrup and salt together in a heavy saucepan.
Cook rapidly to 238° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until they hold stiff peaks.
Pour 1/3 of syrup over egg whites, beating vigorously.
Continue cooking remaining syrup until it reaches 270° or the hard ball stage. Pour over egg white mixture, beating constantly.
Finish beating by hand until mixture is creamy and will hold its shape when dropped from a spoon (about 5 minutes).
Add nuts and flavoring. Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper or pour into a box lined with foil.
Cut into pieces if a box is used.
Store tightly covered.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Use a glass pyrex dish 9 x 13 or larger. Mix black cherry Jello, 3/4 cup hot water, and 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour first layer in pan and let set over night.
Using the cherry Jello mix with 1/2 cup hot water, 1/2 cut cold water and 1/2 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Pour into pan and let set overnight.
Repeat alternating water and milk mixtures until all 7 layers are complete.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt butter.
Saute celery, bell pepper, onion and mushrooms. Add paprika, salt, nutmeg, pepper, pimiento, stock and chicken. Bring to a boil and add spaghetti and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.

title: berniece's applesauce cake
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple and cherry pie filling in casserole dish, mix together.
Spread dry cake over pineapple and cherry layer.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 40 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: I add a little alum to help crispness.
Bring the syrup ingredients to a boil.
Add vegetables.
Heat thoroughly, but do not overcook.
Can in sterile jars.
Makes a crisp pickle.

title: ham or turkey pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple and pecans.
Spread each slice meat with mixture and roll from long side.
Place seam side down in dish.
Cover and chill in refrigerator several hours.
Slice in bite size pinwheels with toothpick stuck through each.
Can be made a few days ahead.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: easiest cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk.
Pour mixture into baking dish containing the melted butter.
On top, pour can of fruit.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Cover with topping mixture.
Bake at 350 for 35 minutes.

title: quick chili
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer until well blended.
This recipe freezes well.

title: chicken curry
directions: Boil chicken in salt water and powdered curry until tender. Take skin off and pick meat off the bone. Thicken the broth.
Cook curry rice.
Serve chicken and gravy over the rice, have oranges, raisins, apple and chutney as side dishes to stack on top.
Serve California vegetables and rolls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the ground chuck, onion, bread, A.1. steak sauce, egg and milk together and shape. Spread the catsup over all the meat loaf.
Sprinkle parsley over the meat loaf.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350° or microwave for approximately 30 minutes or more.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mix and refrigerate. Best if allowed to set overnight.

title: no fat dill dip(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Allow to stand at least
8 hours before serving.
Serve with chips, vegies, etc.

title: coconut creme pie
directions: Sprinkle 2/3 cup coconut into bottom of crust.
Set aside. Spread remaining coconut in an even layer on shallow pan.
Toast at 350° for 7 to 12 minutes or until golden brown, stirring often. Pour milk into medium bowl, add pudding mix and beat with wire whisk for 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Spread whipped topping on pie, then sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix ingredients (except celery), stirring until well mixed, in a small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours, until set. Also, cut celery and refrigerate.
Stuff celery about 1/2 hour before you are ready to serve.

title: cinnamon snails
directions: Trim crusts from bread and spread with cream cheese on each piece.
Roll up and cut into thirds.
Stir sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip each roll into melted butter, then into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Try not to dip ends of roll in butter and sugar.
Place roll, seam side down, on ungreased cookie tray. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: christmas crescent ring
directions: Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and almond extract.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
On ungreased cookie sheet, arrange triangles in a circle with pointed ends out and bottoms (opposite ends) overlapping.
Leave a 3-inch circle in middle.
Spoon cheese mixture onto bottom of triangle, spoon pie filling on top.
Fold 1 triangle over so tip touches bottom corner, press outside edge to seal.
Repeat.
Brush top with milk. Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Roll out pastry 1-inch larger than original size. Spray deep quiche pan with Pam. Line pan with pastry and dust lightly with flour. Beat eggs. Add mayonnaise, cornstarch, Mrs. Dash and nutmeg and mix well, then add rest of ingredients and stir well. Pour into large pastry-lined quiche pan or two regular size pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool before cutting.

title: grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Mix salad dressing and rosemary in shallow bowl.
Add pork, coating well.
Marinate in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours, then drain.
Grill over hot coals for 15 to 20 minutes or until done to taste.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: In large saucepan, combine butterscotch chips and peanut butter; heat until melted and smooth.
Add rice cereal; stir until well coated.
Press half of mixture into a buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Chill in refrigerator while preparing fudge.
Set remaining cereal aside.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water, chocolate chips, sugar, butter and water.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Spread over refrigerated cereal mixture.
Spread remaining cereal over top of chocolate.
Press gently. Refrigerate until firm (about 1 hour).

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt in skillet.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Mix hamburger mixture, egg noodles, soups, corn, pimento and sour cream together.
Put in dish and cook for 30 minutes at 350° or 400°.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs before putting in the oven.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender. Add beaten egg and milk which have been mixed together.
Mix and shape into ball.
Lightly roll pastry into circle 1-inch larger than pie plate.
Pat out air bubbles, fold edges under and crimp.
Prick entire crust before baking. Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Make more than one pie shell.

title: taco rice casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain. Add taco seasoning mix. Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 plus minutes. This recipe freezes well.

title: gazpacho black bean salad
directions: In large bowl, combine beans, corn, rice, cheese, red pepper, celery and green onions.
Set aside.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend butter, brown sugar and flour together as pie dough. Add nuts and coconut.
Mix together.
Put in 9-inch pan; do not roll.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter 2-quart casserole dish.
Add apples, sprinkle with water.
Mix first 6 ingredients with pastry blender.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cover with foil and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar in medium bowl. Add corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie shell. Bake 50 minutes until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, milk, flour and vanilla.
Heat 1 cup sugar, strawberries and water to dissolve sugar.
Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Add mixture to butter.
Pour heated strawberries over mixture.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Blend all ingredients, except corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with corn flakes and butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, Parmesan cheese and green onions. Refrigerate overnight.
Fry and crumble bacon.
Cut up cauliflower and broccoli.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Add bacon.
Mix well.

title: oven fried garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash chicken breasts; remove skin if you like.
Season with salt, pepper and 1/2 of the tablespoon of garlic powder.
Mix flour and corn meal together and coat chicken breasts.
Melt butter on bottom of a baking pan and sprinkle the rest of garlic powder on melted butter.
Place chicken breasts in pan and cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove foil, turn chicken breasts over and bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: pineapple treat
directions: Drain pineapple; coat with confectioners sugar.
Roll in coconut.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Combine flour, Parmesan cheese, paprika, salt, oregano and dry mustard, stirring well.
Dip chicken in milk and dredge in flour mixture.
Heat 1-inch of oil in large skillet.
Add chicken; fry approximately 5 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.

title: debi's swedish brownies
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar.
Add flour to almond flavoring. Add melted butter and beat for 1 minute.
Pour into greased 9 X 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350 for 20 to 30 minutes.
Before baking sprinkle with sugar (red or green for the holidays).
Try 325 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes in a larger pan.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will also need corn dog sticks.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; let stand while preparing remaining salad ingredients.
Gently toss together all ingredients.
Makes 12 servings.

title: dreamy spaghetti
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Put half in a large casserole dish. Mix browned ground beef, tomato sauce and mushrooms.

Set aside. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green pepper and onion. Spread cheese mixture on noodles in dish. Add other half of the noodles. Spread meat mixture over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: nora's quick and easy dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a wire whisk until smooth; add vanilla and spices and stir in.
Stir in melted margarine and fruit.
Pour into a lightly greased dish.
(If desired, you may sprinkle with spices instead of adding to batter.)

title: orange cookies
directions: Ice with 1 box powdered sugar, juice of orange, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon grated rind of orange.
These are drop cookies.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: baked turkey breast
directions: Skin and wash turkey. Cut up onion.
Brush turkey with Texas Pete.
Wrap in foil.
Put in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 12 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat; cook onion, celery and green pepper in a little butter.
Cook noodles and drain.
Combine all ingredients except mushroom soup.
Put into a casserole.
Pour the mushrooms on top. Top with bacon or slices of butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Very good!

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Wash cabbage and separate 12 large leaves.
Drop leaves into boiling salted water, cover and cook 3 minutes.
Drain and dry well.
Combine beef, onion, oats, egg, salt, pepper and milk. Divide into 12 parts and place on cabbage leaves.
Roll leaf around meat and fasten with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.

title: trout almondine
directions: Wash trout; wipe dry with paper towel.
Squeeze lemon juice over inside of trout.
Dip into milk and then flour.
Fry in shortening which is warm.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes on each side over a low fire.
When cooked on one side, keep pouring grease on cooked side.
When flaky, remove to warm platter and keep warm.
Add more butter to pan and saute almonds until golden.
Add remaining ingredients and let it cook down a little.
Pour over trout and garnish with lemon and parsley.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in condensed milk, pudding mix, cold milk, and vanilla until smooth. Fold in 1/2 of the whipped topping. Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish with vanilla wafers. Arrange sliced bananas evenly over wafers. Spread with pudding mixture. Top with remaining whipped topping. Chill.

title: cherry coconut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well. Fold in coconut and Wheaties.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mother's punch
directions: Boil the water and sugar together.
Add rest of ingredients. Add the cold ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 30 people.

title: dove breasts in brown gravy
directions: Lightly
salt
and
pepper dove.
Roll in 1/2 cup flour and brown
in
hot
oil in a Dutch oven.
Remove dove;	add 2 tablespoons
flour	to
the oil and brown to make a roux.
Add onions and saute.
Add water and stir well.
Add dove and cook over
low
heat about 40 minutes or until tender.
Avoid overcooking, as the meat will separate from the bone.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Whip the first 4 ingredients together.
Add salt and flour. Roll dough into ball.
Dip into 2 slightly beaten egg whites, then roll into 2 cups nuts.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Take out of oven and make thumbprint on middle of cookie.
Return to oven for 7 minutes more.
Decorate with colored icing in thumbprint.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Sprinkle garlic salt to taste. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours; drain. Serve with chips.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Place in saucepan with 1/4 cup butter. Heat over medium stove until melted and smooth, stirring often. Place vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over and mix well.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Heat soup with 1/4 cup butter and mix.
Add sour cream.
Grate potatoes.
Layer potatoes, onions, cheese, corn and soup in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Add layer of cheese last. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: goose stuffed with apples
directions: Boil giblets in water until tender.
Chop very fine and add to bread, onion, apples, salt, pepper, garlic and sage or any other seasoning you prefer.
Add water until stuffing is just moistened. Stuff goose and place in roasting pan.
Pour melted butter over goose.
Cover and roast at 325° until tender, about 25 minutes, per pound of meat.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together. Spread on 12-inch platter.
Layer remaining vegetables and cheese in order given.
Sprinkle with taco sauce and decorate top with black olives.
Serve with taco chips.

title: fresh cabbage skillet
directions: Fry bacon until crisp,
drain
and remove.
Add rest of ingredients and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender,
stir
occasionally.
Add 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of sugar and a little of pepper.
Remove to serving dish and
sprinkle
with
crisp bacon crumbled over top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and place in the bottom of a baking dish. Add onions, tomatoes, green peppers, cheese and soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter over low heat.
Add olive oil, parsley, garlic and lemon juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 3 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add shrimp to mixture and let stand about 30 minutes.

title: south of the border black-eyed peas
directions: Sort and wash peas; place in large pot.
Cover with 2-inches water above peas (let soak overnight).
Drain peas.
Add 5 cups water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute garlic and onion in some olive oil until brown.
Add ground meat and cook until crumbly.
Drain fat.
Add tomato paste, the bouillon cubes (crumbled) and flour.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add the wine, water, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Boil rice.
Heat oil; scramble eggs.
Add scallions and meat. Add rice, soy sauce, salt and m.s.g.
Cook 7 minutes.

title: susan's rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine, sugar and salt. Let cool slightly. Cover yeast with 1/2 cup lukewarm water to dissolve. Add beaten egg to margarine, sugar and salt mixture. Dump into flour. Add dissolved yeast; mix well. Cover tightly with foil and place in refrigerator until firm. About 2 to 3 hours before baking time, roll out and cut. Place on greased pan. Brush rolls with melted margarine. Cover and let rise. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding recipe
directions: Butter 6 slices of bread on one side.
Cut in 1-inch cubes (can use more than 6 slices of bread, depending on how thick you want your pudding).
Stir all the rest of the ingredients in the bread cubes and mix well.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake approximately 40 minutes until set.

title: corn medley
directions: Drain corn; mix all veggie ingredients together.
Bring last 5 ingredients to a boil.
Pour liquid ingredients over veggies.
Let set overnight.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain.
Add cheese.
Melt oleo in skillet and add cracker crumbs.
Stir until lightly browned.
In greased 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish, add broccoli and cheese mixture, ending with crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Add salt to 1 gallon boiling water and pour over cucumber cubes.
Let stand 1 week.
Stir each day.
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Add powdered alum to 1 gallon boiling water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Heat together 2 quarts vinegar, 8 pints white sugar and spices.
Drain, reheat and pour over cucumbers for 3 days.
On 4th day, heat syrup and pour over cucumbers that have been placed in sterilized jars. Put lids on and process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Makes 14 pints.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: In skillet cook and crumble the sausage.
Drain well on a paper towel.
In a heavy bottomed pan, melt cheese.
Add milk, cooked sausage and other ingredients.
Serve in a chafing dish with Tostitos.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook the cabbage
leaves until limp in boiling water; let cool.
Combine the salt, pepper, ground meat, rice, onion, egg and poultry seasoning and place in leaf.
Roll up.
Use toothpicks if you have to.
Put the oil in a large frying pan or Dutch oven. Put in the rolls.
Pour the tomato sauce over the rolls.
Combine the brown sugar, water and lemon juice and pour in over the rolls. Simmer, covered, 1 hour, basting occasionally. Add more tomato sauce, if you use chicken filling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken stupendous
directions: Sprinkle dry soup in well-greased casserole skillet.
Put raw rice over this.
Lay meat over rice.
Mix soup and water; pour over meat.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, covered the first hour. Remove cover; sprinkle with paprika to brown the last 1/2 hour.

title: beverly's roast beef casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and green pepper in oil until brown.
Add mushrooms and tomatoes; simmer.
Add gravy and simmer 10 minutes. Combine cooked noodles with beef mixture; add pepper to taste. Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosted fruit pie
directions: Cook together the pineapple, jello and sugar for 1 minute; then chill.
Whip cream and lemon juice, then add chilled and thickened fruit mixture.
Use baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.

title: gooie butter cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, butter and egg with fork until well blended. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, forming about 1 inch rim up side of pan.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in mixing bowl; add flour, sugar and milk. Mix well.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour in baking dish.
Preheat oven to 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
This is great with vanilla ice cream.
You can also put chopped pecans on top before baking.

title: kway lude
directions: Mix equal portions of all ingredients in 1-gallon jug and mix well.
Serve as a shot or pour over ice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir pudding into undrained pineapple.
Add nuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: energy drink
directions: Mix well.
Three times the ingredients makes 1 gallon.
Drink 1/2 cup at a time.

title: instant boiled custard
directions: Mix 1 quart milk in pudding.
Mix well and add the rest of the milk and sugar and beat for 2 minutes.
Add whipped cream and vanilla and beat for 1 minute.
Chill at least 3 hours before you need it or overnight.

title: beauty shop pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Toast coconut and pecans in butter (broil until brown).
Layer cream cheese mixture and coconut mixture in graham cracker crusts.
Top with hot caramel topping.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hot cheese
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour, salt and paprika.
Shape into balls; freeze on cookie sheet.
Store in freezer.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and flour and mix together.
Roll teaspoonfuls of dough, pat them out and crisis-cross with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Bone and skin chicken breast.
Marinate in garlic and enough buttermilk to cover.
Dip in flour and deep fry.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together; spread on a platter or tray.
Spread salsa sauce on next.
Sprinkle browned hamburg over salsa sauce.
Sprinkle chopped green pepper and tomatoes over top and then grated Cheddar cheese.
You can add other vegetables, if you wish.

title: pork tenderloin with tarragon sauce
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch slices.
Place meat between sheets of wax paper.
Flatten each piece.
Salt and pepper slices and brush with mustard on both sides.
Melt margarine in skillet and brown the meat on medium heat until pink color is gone, about 5 minutes per side.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Sprinkle tarragon in skillet; add broth and boil about 2 minutes.
Add cream.
Boil and whisk until thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour sauce over meat or serve separately.
Sauce is good over rice with the meat slices.

title: bim-bim
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in medium pan.
Cook over medium heat until it comes to a full, rolling boil.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until
well blended.
Stir in oats, 1 cup at a time.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let sit until firm.
Store loosely in airtight containers.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Remove stem; cut tomatoes in half and place on a shallow baking dish.
Top each tomato half with a tablespoon of grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; turn broiler on and lightly brown the top.

title: old timey buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form cakes.
Add enough oatmeal to bind.
Dredge in cracker crumbs.
Bake on cookie sheet in two tablespoons of oil at 375° for 25 minutes.
Turn cakes and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Oil a jelly roll pan or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine chocolate and marshmallow cream in large bowl and set aside.
Mix sugar, butter and milk in a 3-quart heavy pot, stirring to combine well. Gradually bring to boil over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Dip a pastry brush in cold water and wash down the sides of pot.
Continue to boil, stirring constantly, without touching spoon to sides of pot, for 5 minutes, then pour mixture over chocolate mixture and add salt and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Then stir in nuts.
Spread on a cookie sheet or pan and let stand until firm.
Cut into squares and store airtight.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in microwave.
Butter a casserole.
Place broccoli in bottom.
Make sauce of soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spoon little sauce over broccoli.
Place cooked chicken on top.
Pour rest of sauce over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Line bottom and sides of a 10 x 8-inch baking dish with mixture of first 3 ingredients.
Spread with cream, marshmallow, sugar mixture and top with pie filling.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: favorite pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Stir in light brown sugar.
Mix in evaporated milk, broken pecans, salt, well beaten eggs (one at a time) and vanilla.
Have pie shell ready; pour filling into crust. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until firm.
Be sure pie is firm to touch around the edge, but slightly soft in center.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in covered jar.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of boiling water.

title: cold spaghetti
directions: Break spaghetti in half and cook according to package directions; drain well.
Place green pepper, cucumber and tomatoes into blender and blend until smooth (or a chunkier consistency, if desired).
Mix spaghetti, Italian dressing, blender mix and Salad Supreme in a large bowl, saving a little of the Salad Supreme to sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Lightly oil a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and place in layers the first 4 ingredients.
Slice butter over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve cold or warm with Cool Whip, whipped cream or ice cream.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash and clean chicken.
Place in baking pan.
Pour butter over chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and oregano to taste. Place 1 small onion in cavity of chicken.
Peel and quarter potatoes; peel and cut carrots in half.
Place around chicken. Cut or slice second onion and place over potatoes and carrots. Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Fifteen minutes before done, remove foil to brown chicken.

title: chinese "fried" cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Heat oil in frypan.
Add cabbage, bacon bits and soy sauce.
Stir until covered with oil.
Turn heat to low. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally for about 5 minutes or until tender.
Fresh spinach can be substituted for cabbage.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Dill pickles can be purchased at Sam's or Turrentines for $2.99.
Drain vinegar from the pickles and replace with fresh water.
Let set overnight.	Drain again and fill with fresh water again.
Cover with ice.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain off water and replace with the 8 cups of sugar and 4 cups vinegar. Also the pickling spices as desired.
Pour over the pickles in the gallon jug and seal it.
Turn upside down (in the refrigerator) until sugar melts.
They are ready - wonderful, crisp and economical.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in the order given in large glass bowl.
Top with Miracle Whip, covering from side to side. Chill overnight; garnish with bacon bits and cheese.

title: maple-apple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a 9-inch round skillet.
Stir in syrup and mix well.
Core apples.
Slice in 1/2-inch rounds and arrange in the syrup, placing an end slice skin side down.
Arrange cherries in and around apple slices. Peel remaining apple pieces and chop or grate to make about 2/3 cup.

title: stromboli
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet, spread bread dough and layer the remaining ingredients in the middle of the dough.
Fold the sides of the dough up to cover the contents and seal the edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Pour into greased square cake pan.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over cake mixture. Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together well and shape into 8 cakes.
Fry in hot butter until golden brown.

title: coffee can yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add ginger and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add rest of sugar, salt, oil and evaporated milk.
Add flour gradually until dough is heavy and not sticky.
Knead on a floured board for 5 minutes. Divide and place into two greased one-pound coffee cans or one 2 pound can. Put lids on.
Let rise in warm place until dough pushes against top.
Remove lids and bake in a 350° oven until done (1 pound can equals 45 minutes; 2 pound can equals 1 hour).
If top gets too brown while baking, drape foil over top.
Brush with butter for soft crust.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch; add milk, a half cup at a time, mixing well.
Add eggs and corn; mix.
Pour into a well-greased Pyrex dish; dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
(One teaspoon vanilla may be added to mix.) Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until it sets up so that a knife inserted into it comes out clean.

title: meat loaf hamburgers
directions: In a large bowl combine hamburger and rest of ingredients together, mixing well.
Make into patties and either fry or grill to your liking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream oleo; then add the sugar slowly and cream well.
