Add egg yolks one at a time and beat.
Add flour sifted with baking powder alternately with milk, beating well.
Add flavoring; then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: banana tea bread
directions: In a shallow bowl mash bananas.
In large bowl beat eggs.
Add melted butter, sugar and brown sugar, then add molasses and 1 3/4 cups flour.
When all ingredients are blended, add bananas.
Add 1 3/4 cups flour to mixture.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Then add nuts, raisins, apricots and dates.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small mixing bowl, using back of spoon, combine sugar and margarine.
Add egg, vanilla, cinnamon, cloves, ginger, nutmeg, allspice and salt.
Using an electric mixer at low speed, beat until combined.

title: crab and potato chowder
directions: Cut potatoes into bite-sized pieces.
Melt butter over medium heat in 3 quart saucepan.
Add leeks, turn heat to low.
Cover and allow to cook slowly 3 to 4 minutes or until softened.
Add vermouth, water, potatoes, salt and thyme.
Bring to boil.
Turn heat to low, cover and cook until potatoes are fork tender (about 20 minutes).
Add milk and crab meat.
Heat through but do not boil.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve.

title: shrimp dip(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart microwave-proof casserole.
Use Cook cycle and cook 3 to 4 minutes or until warm, stirring once during cooking time.
Stir.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: turkey or chicken pot pie
directions: Let pie crust thaw while mixing ingredients.
Mix all ingredients; don't dilute soup.
Place in pie crust; take other pie crust and place on top; crimp edges together.
Brush butter or spray Pam on top crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° on a cookie sheet until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Combine together.
Shape dough into balls (rounded teaspoonful for each).
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
With candy Kiss, press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.
Makes about 35 cookies.

title: oreo cake
directions: First Layer: Mix melted butter with 1/2 of the Oreo cookies. Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oyster soup
directions: Garnish:
Croutons (in 1/2-inch dices) seasoned with olive oil, parsley, garlic and Parmesan cheese.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: sloppy joe chocolate cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together in an electric mixer.
Add egg, vanilla and sour milk, mixing until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Mix in zucchini last.
Spoon into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle top of cake with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Soak the beans overnight.
Put the beans, ham hock and beef bone in 2 quarts water.
Cook 45 minutes.
Cut bacon and onion into 5 pieces and fry until onions are browned.
Add the bacon and onions to the beans.
Add the diced potatoes, salt, saffron and sliced sausage.
Continue cooking until the potatoes are well done.

title: beef roast
directions: Wash, salt and pepper roast.
Put in a baking pan.
Add 1 cup water and onion soup mix.
Bake, covered, on 350° until meat is tender.
Add mushroom soup, celery soup, carrots and potatoes. Bake until potatoes and carrots are tender.

title: oyster stew 1993
directions: Brown oysters in margarine until oysters curl.
Mix remaining ingredients in with oysters and heat.
Serves 2.

title: rabbit
directions: Heat pork grease.
Roll rabbit in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Place in hot grease.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach dessert
directions: Melt the margarine in the cake pan (9 x 13-inch) and pour the peaches in the cake pan with the butter.
In a bowl , mix together the flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour this over the peaches and butter and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; add salt.
Let stand 1 hour, then squeeze out liquid. Mix all together with remaining ingredients.
Do not reduce sugar or slaw won't be crisp.
Put in Ziploc bag and freeze.
You can freeze for 3 to 4 months.
Delicious!

title: hot fruit dessert
directions: Grate orange and lemon into brown sugar.
Cut orange and lemon into thin slices.
Arrange all fruits in layers.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Heat on top of stove until very hot.
Serve warm with sour cream.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, vinegar and water.
Cook until forms ball in cold water.
Remove and add butter and soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Make into balls.

title: potato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes, sugar, milk, salt and oil.
Let cool.
Add soda to cottage cheese or yogurt.
Mix together.
Add eggs.
Add 5 cups of flour; beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour until ready to knead.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Let raise until double.
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes.
Divide into 5 portions.
Shape into loaves.
Put into greased pans; let raise until double.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Brush tops with butter.

title: bean patties
directions: Mash dried cooked beans or peas with broth.
Add bread crumbs to beans.
Stir well until mixture becomes manageable.
Add seasoning and egg and form into patties.
Heat shortening and add patties.
When brown, turn and brown on the other side.
May substitute 1 cup of leftover peas or beans for the can.

title: sherylle's super corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in cupcake pans at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: no egg or butter chocolate cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, salt, soda and cocoa; make a well.
Add the oil, vinegar, vanilla and cold water; stir until blended. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach feta shells
directions: Cook shells according to package. Drain and set aside.

title: chili-n-beans
directions: Mix together and simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the red raspberry jello, 1 cup boiling water and 1/4 cup cold water.
While this mixture chills, mix cranberries, orange (ground), apple (chopped fine), crushed pineapple, sugar and chopped pecans.
Fold this mixture into chilled jello.
Chill until set.

title: easy broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli, onions and peppers in boiling water until tender; drain.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour in broccoli mixture.
Add cheese and bacon.
Blend or mix together the milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper; pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place chicken breasts in a saucepan and cover with water. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain, skin and debone chicken.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cut into 12 strips and set aside.

title: dutch oven roast
directions: Melt fat in Dutch oven.
Add meat and brown well on all sides. Add water, salt and diced onions.
Cover and place in a moderate oven at 350°; cook for 2 hours.
Add prepared vegetables.
Cover and cook another hour or until tender.

title: queen cake(this cake is fit for a queen.)
directions: Mix Spry, salt and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add sugar gradually until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each time.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times and add to mixture, alternating with milk.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove and add following topping.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake according to directions. Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake cake 30 minutes.
About 5 minutes before cake is done, place pineapple, its liquid and sugar in pan.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Remove cake from oven and using a fork, make holes over entire cake.
Let cake cool completely.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Spread over entire cake.
Spread whipped topping over pudding.
Sprinkle with pecans and coconut.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt at low temperature, 1 stick butter, milk and water.
Mix yeast, salt, sugar and 4 cups flour.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture.
Add the eggs and another cup of the flour.
May mix this with a mixer until smooth.
Using a spoon, add rest of the flour (up to 1 1/2 cups).
Let rise until double.

title: spice air freshener
directions: Mix ingredients and roll.
Use any shape cookie cutter and have fun!

title: raisin bran refrigerator muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Then add the eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Cover with foil. Don't stir when you remove some for baking.

title: milk chocolate peanut butter bark
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt milk chocolate chips and peanut butter chips, stirring constantly until smooth.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour into prepared pan; spread.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Before serving, break into pieces.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Yields about 1 pound candy.

title: terri's and taylor's hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Brown onions in small portion of butter or margarine.
Pour in soups and sour cream; mix together.
Melt 1 stick butter or margarine and pour with other mixture.
Mix in cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Then top with crushed cornflakes that have been moistened with butter or margarine.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and vanilla. Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Blend in water, stir in flour, mixing well. Add pecans.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, flour and sugar together like pie crust.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°, then beat eggs and add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Mix together and add lemon juice.
Pour on top of baked crust and bake again for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into bars and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Delicious.

title: pumpkin waffles
directions: In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, spices, salt and sugar.
In a medium bowl, combine the pumpkin, milk, egg yolks and melted butter and mix well.
Make a well in dry ingredients; add the pumpkin mixture and stir until combined. In a medium bowl, beat the egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold them gently into the batter just until blended.
Cook the waffles in a preheated waffle iron according to manufacturer's directions.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix in sugar until dissolved. Add pineapple juice, lemonade and almond extract.
Add 3 quarts cold water.

title: 'coon
directions: Clean raccoon.
Place in water with salt and parboil.
Put in baking container raccoon seasoned with salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 500° for one hour.
Serve two days after cooking for better flavor (taste).

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling in 3-quart saucepan.
Add broccoli, celery and onion.
Cover and cook until tender, about 10 minutes (do not drain).
Place in blender and blend until uniform consistency.

title: portuguese rice
directions: Put lid on and cook on low for approximately 1 hour.
Stir twice only (never again).
"Pray over it."
This is a dry rice. Leftovers may be fried crisp.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Tear lettuce and put in large bowl; cut up cauliflower and add to bowl. Fry bacon and crumble over lettuce. Boil eggs and chop up (or can be sliced if preferred). Add about 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Add about 4 or 5 heaping tablespoons Miracle Whip; mix all together. (You may add more or less Miracle Whip.) Serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook long grain wild rice by directions on box.
Put in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion soup over rice.
Mix well.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Mix soups and oleo in a saucepan and heat until smooth.
Pour all over the chicken and rice.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Mix slaw, onions, sunflower seeds, almonds and noodles. Sprinkle beef seasoning; mix well.
Add oil, sugar and vinegar; mix well.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper; coat meat.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in frying pan; brown meat.
Add garlic, onion and mushrooms; fry until golden.
Move meat and onion to one side of pan.
To other side of pan add 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons flour; blend.
Add tomato paste and beef broth.
Mix well.
Cook until thickened.
Add sour cream and heat through; do not boil.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over noodles (or rice).

title: chili
directions: Brown meat first; drain, then add other ingredients.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Add all ingredients.
Whip with wire whisk.

title: pollo guidado
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet; place chicken, bone side down, in skillet.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add chopped vegetables and spices (not tomatoes and jalapenos).
Simmer 5 minutes, then add 1 cup of broth and salt.
Turn breasts over and cover for 15 minutes. Remove cover and bone the chicken, one breast at a time, and break into 3 or 4 large pieces.
Return to broth and vegetables.
Test for right amount of salt and spices; add more if needed.
Add the tomatoes, jalapenos and rest of broth; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
The liquid should cook down a lot; the final consistency should be of chicken in a thick tomato sauce.
Serve with arroz and frijoles refritos with corn tortillas.

title: classic rice salad
directions: Chop pickles and onions real fine. Mix all ingredients together and keep salad refrigerated.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix sugar and Miracle Whip together.
Add other ingredients. Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until it springs back.

title: anna's chicken soup
directions: Wash chicken well.
Into a large pot, put chicken.
Bring to a boil; skim off anything that comes to the top.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Remove all ingredients to a plate.
Into simmering broth, add 1/2 cup rice.
After 1/2 hour, add 1 pound spinach which has been cooked 1 minute, drained well and chopped.
Cut up small amount of chicken breast.
Add to broth. Simmer for 5 minutes, then serve.
Instead of rice, small size pasta could be used.
This pasta cooks in about 3 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine biscuit mix, sour cream and club soda.
Mix well and knead 10 times on floured surface using biscuit mix.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick and cut 2 1/2-inch round.
Place on baking sheet 1-inch apart.
Brush biscuits before baking and after baking with melted butter.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 16 biscuits.

title: so-good sweet potato casserole
directions: Spray Pam on 2-quart casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°. Put the sweet potatoes, half and half, egg, brown sugar, spice and salt in food processor and blend
until smooth.
Stir in pineapple.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows and nuts around top of casserole.
Bake 15 more minutes.
Delicious with turkey dinner!

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls approximately 1 inch in diameter.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Melt 1/2 block of paraffin and 1 bag chocolate chips.
Dip balls in mixture until coated.
Let chill.
Enjoy!

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt or tube pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls, getting some between the rolls. Melt butter; mix with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls, being sure to get mixture down in between rolls.
Sprinkle nuts all over.
Cover.
Leave on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: california chicken casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on box.
Thaw broccoli in boiling water.
Drain well.
Place rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan and layer broccoli over rice.
Cut chicken in cubes
and layer over the broccoli.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, milk and cheese. Spread over casserole and sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
You may substitute chicken broth in place of milk if you wish.
Do not salt the chicken when cooking.

title: jellied cranberry port sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan (2 quarts or larger).
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until all the berries have burst.
Allow to cool.
Then spoon into a 1-quart mold or bowl.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
Unmold and serve.
Yield:
approximately 1 quart.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter in a large bowl.
Work in the powdered sugar and cracker crumbs with a wooden spoon until combined thoroughly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside. Melt chocolate pieces.
Quickly spread melted chocolate over the top of the peanut butter mixture.
Chill until firm, but not too cold.
Cut into small squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: brenda's banana pudding
directions: Stir together all ingredients and pour over layered bananas and vanilla wafers.
Chill.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks and other ingredients and fold in egg whites last.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans at 325° until done.

title: shrimp-fra-diavolo
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in sauce pan 3 minutes.
Add pepper flakes and saute another minute.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, simmer until shrimp is translucent, about 5 minutes.

title: company waffles
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir in milk and melted butter.
Add liquids to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Use about 1/2 cup for a round waffle pan. Makes great light waffles.

title: spicy homemade sausage
directions: Combine ground beef, meat cure mix, ground pepper, red pepper, mustard seed, garlic powder and liquid smoke.
Mix well and chill 8 hours or overnight.
Shape meat mixture into five 5 x 3-inch logs. Wrap logs individually in cheesecloth; tie ends with string.
Place on rack in a shallow baking pan; bake 6 hours in a gas oven at 200°.
Chill 8 hours and store in refrigerator.
Serve garnished with lettuce and apple.
May be frozen.

title: reta's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients; top with bacon.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter until crumbly.
Press in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix with mixer 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt and mix well; add mayonnaise and milk, then add flour and soda (baking).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cake can be iced to your preference.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour and dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Add fruit cocktail last.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine first
three
ingredients.
Salt
and pepper to taste. Put in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Slice eggs over this. Mix butter, milk,
baking
powder
and
flour
and
pour
over chicken mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until crust is brown.

title: deviled crab eggs
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks, put 1/2 of them in a bowl and mash well.
Discard the other half.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper and crab meat.
Mix well. Stuff egg whites.
Sprinkle tops lightly with Old Bay seasoning. Chill before serving.

title: sweet mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes excellent dressing for salads, sandwiches, pork or chicken.

title: cottage butterhorns
directions: Cream all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Divide dough into 3 equal parts.
Allow to sit at room temperature until easy to handle.
Roll each into a 10-inch diameter circle. Cut each circle into 12 pie-shaped pieces.
Roll up starting with wide end.
Place on lightly buttered baking sheets.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack. Yields 36.

title: john's horsefeed cereal
directions: Mix oats, wheat bran, wheat germ, Grape-Nuts and raisins in a large bowl.
Melt margarine and add brown sugar or honey.
Pour over dry mix and mix with hands to coat the cereal.
Arrange on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 4 minutes.
Stir well and bake an additional 4 minutes.
Cool and store in plastic bags in refrigerator or freezer.
Allow 1/3 cup per serving with milk and extra fruit, if desired.

title: chicken veggie flautas
directions: Combine cheese, chicken, broccoli, picante sauce and green onions.
Brush one side of each tortilla with melted butter. Place 1/4 cup of cheese mixture down center of unbuttered side of tortilla.
Roll up; place seam side down on foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for 14 to 16 minutes, or until brown and crispy.
Serve with sour cream and more picante sauce.

title: bubble bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan.
Place rolls in bottom of pan.
Top with light brown sugar, then pudding, sugar and cinnamon, melted butter and nuts.
Let stand 8 hours, then cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spanish cornbread
directions: Beat eggs, add oil, milk, sugar, flour and meal.
Add chopped ingredients, cheese and corn.
Stir well.
Grease a large iron skillet and sprinkle with meal.
Heat slightly.
Pour in batter. Bake at 400° about 45 minutes or until browned.

title: chamomile tea
directions: Pour hot water over the flowers and steep for at least 5 minutes.
Strain and sweeten to taste.
Serves 1.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Place beef in glass or plastic bowl.
Mix soy sauce, Sake, oil, ginger root, sugar and garlic.
Pour over beef, cover and refrigerate (stirring occasionally), at least 1 hour.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: portuguese potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish.
Add onion and half of cheese. Cover with bread cubes, sprinkle with pimento, parsley, paprika and garlic.
Add remaining cheese.
Pour margarine over entire dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: polynesian meatballs
directions: Combine and shape into balls; bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, chill then add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: artichoke seafood dip
directions: Drain artichokes and puree with cream cheese and horseradish. Add mayonnaise and shrimp or crab.
Thin with yogurt or sour cream.
May be served without seafood.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes until done on 350 degrees.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Chop and quarter apples; fill crock-pot level full.
Mix dry ingredients with apples and let set overnight.
Cook 4 hours on high temperature.

title: lemon cool whip pie
directions: Mix up real good.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: Cut meat into 4 pieces; brown in Dutch oven or heavy pan in 2 tablespoons fat.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup boiling water.
Add garlic powder, bay leaf and thyme to meat.
Cover and cook slowly until tender (1 hour).
Add applesauce, carrots, potatoes and onions.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add apple and cook 10 minutes.
Remove meat, vegetables and fruit to platter.
Skim off fat.
Thicken with cornstarch and cook until thick.
Add Kitchen Bouquet.
Good if put meat and vegetables into gravy and serve.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions, baking in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar, milk and marshmallows in saucepan. Heat until melted.
Add coconut, stirring, until well blended. Spread over warm cake.
Frost with chocolate frosting. Refrigerate.

title: hearty chicken soup
directions: Cover chicken in pot with water and boil until done. Remove chicken from bone. Place bouillon cubes in pot of water chicken was cooked in, pour in potatoes and onion. Let cook for about 10 minutes. Add tomatoes, mixed vegetables, salt, pepper and tabasco sauce. (May sprinkle in garlic salt if desired for taste.) Cover and cook for 10-15 minutes on medium - low or until potatoes are tender.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets.
Using beet juice, add vinegar to make 1 cup liquid.
Add sugar and salt to taste.
Bring to boil.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add beets, celery and onion.
Refrigerate.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring juice and Sweet 'N Low to a boil.
Add beets.
Turn off heat and let cool.
Store for up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chateau potatoes
directions: Place all ingredients in mashed potatoes. Place in large casserole dish. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashion stack cake
directions: Roll each layer very thin and bake in a 350° preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Put apple butter in between layers.
Makes about 9 or 10 layers.
(Best with homemade apple butter.)

title: crackers
directions: Knead five minutes;
roll very thin.
Cut; bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Plain - dill - garlic flavors.

title: scotch bars
directions: Melt butter and stir in sugar until smooth.
Beat eggs into mixture. Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Add to sugar, butter and eggs. Add nuts and flavoring. Bake and cut in squares while warm. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate coated coconut balls
directions: Melt margarine slowly.
Add milk.
Stir in sugar and salt. Add coconut and pecans.
Chill until it can be handled easily. Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat and dip each ball in chocolate.
Remove quickly and place on wax paper.

title: one dish pork chops and potatoes
directions: Place peeled and sliced potatoes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix can of soup with potatoes.
Salt and pepper pork chops to taste. Place on top of potatoes.
Bake in 375° oven until chops are done, about 45 minutes.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix flour and salt, cut in Crisco and add the water.
Work with hands to form a soft, firm dough.
Cut in half.
Roll out bottom crust, place in pie pan and add fruit of your choice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dabs of margarine.
Cover with remaining crust, cutting slits into top crust for steam to escape.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, reducing heat to 350° for another 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple bread casserole
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add unbeaten eggs and beat until well combined.
Add crushed pineapple, then fold in bread cubes.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and decorate with pineapple rings and cherries.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm with ham or chicken.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Cook 30 minutes at 375°.

title: old-fashioned fig preserve cake
directions: Beat together the oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add remaining dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Fold in fig preserves.
Pour into Bundt pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325°, approximately 60 minutes or until knife inserted in middle of cake comes out clean (ovens vary).
You have a delicious fruit/pound cake.

title: milk chocolate cheesecake
directions: Grease pan.
Combine cocoa packet in cake mix with 1/4 cup cake mix, cream cheese and melted chocolate.
Beat two minutes, then add eggs and whipping cream.

title: canned creamed crab
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Drain crab and slice larger pieces.
Mix soup, sour cream, green pepper, onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard in a medium bowl.
Fold in crab.
Spoon mixture into ungreased individual casseroles.
Mix butter and bread crumbs together in small bowl.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: porcupine meatballs(microwave tender cooker or oven)
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients except tomato sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Roll in 9 (2-inch) balls.
Pour tomato sauce over meatballs in casserole.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: brandied carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole pan.
Mix eggs, sugar, butter, flour and milk.
Add brandy, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add carrots.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: pork chop-apple casserole
directions: In skillet, brown chops in oil, both sides.
Pour off drippings and reserve 1/4 cup.
Season chops with pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.

title: pizza primavera
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Steam all vegetables (except tomatoes) until barely tender.
Immerse in ice water to stop cooking.
Drain well and reserve.
Shape dough any way you like; brush dough with olive oil.
Top with the shredded cheeses.
Arrange the vegetables and tomatoes on top of the cheeses; sprinkle with the green onions. Season to taste with salt and pepper; drizzle with the remaining olive oil.
Bake at 500° for about 10 minutes, until crust is golden.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and tarragon.
Slice and serve.

title: fruit delight
directions: Combine all fruits in large bowl.
Sprinkle pudding over top of fruit and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: turkey roll
directions: Combine all except broccoli and cheese (save part of tomato sauce for top).
On sheet of foil, pat meat mixture to 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle broccoli and cheese over meat and roll up. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, wrapped in foil.
Open and top with sauce.
Brown in oven.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix and bake in 2 cake pans for 30-35 minutes, ice when cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Form ball.
Roll in finely chopped nuts if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Saute chicken in oil 8 minutes, remove from pot and set aside. Saute onion and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add chilies, pepper, cumin and cook 3 minutes.
Add white beans, broth and chicken, bring to boil, then reduce and simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Cook until cheese melts stirring continually.
Serve with green onions and flour tortilla shells on the side.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours.
If desired, mash potatoes with masher before serving.
Serve topped with chopped chives.
Servings: 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Add cheese, mayonnaise, eggs, soup and onion.
Combine well; pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar, pineapple, eggs, soda, flour and pecans. Bake at 350° until done.
Mix together cream cheese, oleo and confectioners sugar.
Ice cooled cake.

title: coffee can cake
directions: Mix all ingredients into a batter.
Pour batter into 3 (1 pound) coffee cans and bake 45 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar until smooth. Stir in lemon peel and mandarin syrup.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread this mixture evenly in the bottom of the prepared crust.
Press mandarins into the cream cheese layer.
Mix 2 cups milk with pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk for one minute.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Gently stir in raspberries and 1 cup whipped topping, spoon mixture over mandarins.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and fresh mint.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ham-broccoli rolls
directions: Top each ham slice with slice of cheese.
Place 1/4 of cooked broccoli on each.
In heavy saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, salt, horseradish, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Combine egg yolk and pineapple juice.
Blend into butter mixture. Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbling.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon over broccoli.
Roll ham and cheese around broccoli; serve with wooden picks.
Place rolls in shallow baking dish.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°. Reheat remaining sauce, adding milk if necessary.
Spoon hot mustard sauce over ham rolls.
Garnish with pineapple slices and spiced crab apples.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk and butter in heavy saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat; beat until mixture begins to thicken and cool.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan; cool.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Soak zucchini and onion in large bowl overnight.

title: bar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Add to other mixture.
Spread in greased 13 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with marshmallows and return to oven until puffy and beginning to melt.
Remove from oven.
Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter together and add Rice Krispies.
Stir well. Spread over marshmallows.
Cool.
Cut in squares when cold.
Keep refrigerated.
Freezes nicely.

title: sister froud coconut cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 350° oven.
Ice with Seven-Minute Icing with coconut.
This is a very moist cake.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Put in bottom of dish.
Make dressing, using 1/2 of the liquid called for.
Put on top.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of milk.
Pour over dressing.
Partially cook broccoli.
Put on top of soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beltline burritos
directions: Brown together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients. In saucepan, heat enchilada sauce, V-8 juice, tomato sauce and brown gravy.
Chop up lettuce and tomatoes.
Spread meat mixture on tortillas; add a little chopped lettuce and tomatoes and roll up. Place in a large baking dish or roasting pan and cover with heated sauce.
Sprinkle cheeses over burritos.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: almond butter toffee(microwave)
directions: Line 9 x 9-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Sprinkle almonds in pan.
Rub top (about 1/2-inch) of 2-quart microwave bowl with the butter.
Place butter in bottom of bowl.
Pour sugar directly on the butter (avoid getting on sides of bowl).
Add salt and water. Cook on High for 7 minutes.
This is only starting time.
Keep adding time, 30 second intervals until candy is color of brown sugar or brown butter.
Pour mixture over almonds.
Do not scrape bowl; cool.
Top with melted chocolate.
When chocolate sets, lift foil out of pan and break into pieces.

title: coconut-pecan cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to directions on the box.
When mixed, add the can of coconut/pecan icing to the batter.
Scrape batter into a
bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake as directed on the box of cake mix.
Test with a toothpick or cake tester to see whether it is done.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on a rack to cool.
No frosting necessary.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion. Drain. Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together and place into a casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fried jalapenos
directions: Slit jalapenos down the side.
Remove seeds and membranes without tearing the peppers.
Stuff each pepper with about 1/2 teaspoon cheese.
Mix eggs and milk, beating well.
Roll pepper in flour then in egg mixture and again in flour.
Set jalapeno peppers aside to allow coating to set.
Heat oil to 350°.
Fry peppers until brown.
(No longer than 1 minute.)
Serve with sour cream.

title: crab dip
directions: Dissolve gelatine in the cold water.
Heat soup to warm. Remove from stove.
Add gelatine and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased mold and chill 8 hours. Serve with crackers, chips or vegies.

title: large brisket roast
directions: Marinate the above overnight.
Roll in foil and cook real slow (200°) for 6 to 8 hours.
For small roast, use less ingredients.

title: rosetta ravioli
directions: Prepare ravioli according to directions.
Drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover top with Mozzarella cheese.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 20 minutes.
Place under broiler until cheese is lightly browned.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Layer above ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole pan in the order given, refried beans first.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with nacho chips and watch it disappear.

title: bread stuffing(three quarts for 12 pound turkey)
directions: Melt butter in large heavy skillet.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in some bread crumbs.
Heat, stirring to prevent excessive browning.
Turn into deep bowl.
Mix in remaining ingredients lightly.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook bacon.
Put strained beans in pot.
Cover beans and bacon with cold water until beans are soft.
Put in strainer fixed on a 3-quart pot and separate beans, bacon and broth.
Put broth in pot, set beans aside and throw out bacon.
In small frying pan, melt butter and add flour.
Add to broth.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add beans.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add ham pieces. Simmer.

title: mom's best ever apple butter
directions: Slice up apples; core, skins, seeds and all.
Layer in large size pressure cooker or I use turkey roasters for oven method.
My grandmother and mother did this on top of stove using big pressure cooker.
I adapted it to my ovens and use 2 turkey roasters for 1/2 bushel of apples.
One will work with 1/4 bushel.
Layer apples, alternating with the 5 pounds of regular sugar.
